title: escalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a large casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion, celery and pepper.
Add soup, broth, mushrooms and boned chicken.
Cook and drain noodles. Layer in casserole dish with chicken mixture and grated cheese. Top with grated cheese and bake 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: maple pecan bars
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour with 1/3 cup brown sugar in a bowl. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix and add
to jello.	Pour 1/2 into 12 x 8-inch dish. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Spread
with 1 pint of sour cream.
Spoon remaining fruit mixture over all.

title: corinne's swedish meatballs(from bombay, 1965)
directions: Mix all ingredients; knead until tight.
Make small balls. Brown in skillet with small amount Mazola until crusty.
Put into large saucepan in which are 2 cups boiling water and 2 beef bouillons.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove some of broth; stir in flour to make gravy.
Pour pack into pan; reheat.
Serve with scalloped potatoes or egg noodles, or, if buffet, with potato salad.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
In a 2nd bowl, combine the next 3 ingredients.
Mix both bowls together and add carrots and pineapple.
Mix well; add the rest of the ingredients.
Blend well; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 (8 or 9-inch) round or one 13 x 9-inch.

title: nena peggy's cranberry salad
directions: This is easy and quick.
Just mix it and put it in the fridge!

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool Aid in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 24.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork; add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, until tender.
Drain pineapple; save liquid.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and catsup.
Add to meat; stir until thickened.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender, but not over done. Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt and set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until well blended and smooth.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate morsels.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Remove immediately and cook on wire racks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add package of seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Stir together well. Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add pinto beans (remove fat).
Stir together and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Prepare salad shells according to directions.
Prepare veggies.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into long, greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.

title: honey and marmalade glaze(microwave)
directions: Place honey and marmalade in 1 cup measure and heat on High for 1 1/2 minutes; stir.
Baste ham while it is cooking.
Serve ham with extra glaze.
Makes 1/4 cup of glaze.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in jar.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Heat Crisco oil in frying pan.
Put beef cubes in hot oil. Brown on all sides.
Add soup and sweet and sour sauce.
Add onion, finally season to taste.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with/over rice.

title: lemon cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 1 1/2-inch layer cake pans.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Beat shortening, sugar, lemon rind, juice and eggs at high speed on electric mixer, about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, at low speed, beginning and ending with flour.
Scrape bowl frequently.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: bachelor dinner
directions: Put rice in bowl.
Top with choice of meat and egg.
Mix together and eat up.
Yum!
Yum!
Hot biscuits would go good with this quick meal.

title: corn and pea potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cool.
Add onion, frozen corn and frozen peas to potatoes.
Blend mayonnaise and yogurt together for dressing.
Can mix more if needed.
Mix dressing with potatoes. Sprinkle with dill weed and Spike seasoning.
Extremely easy and quick!
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fresh peas
directions: What more can I say?

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Work together the flour, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Work these ingredients together very good.
Then mix separately the water, egg and vinegar.
Add this to the flour mixture and mix well. Divide into balls for single pie crusts.

title: busy-day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in fat.
Combine with remaining ingredients; season to taste.
Place in covered 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: doris' pot roast
directions: Season meat with pepper and salt and brown in drippings.
Mix other ingredients and add to pot.
Cover tightly and cook 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Thicken liquid.

title: snappy spinach dip
directions: In a bowl, blend all ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Place in round rye bread with center cut out.
Serve with bread pieces or crackers.

title: mexican meat with cornbread topping
directions: Cook meat until browned; add rice, tomatoes, salt, pepper, chili powder and onion.
Mix well, breaking meat and tomatoes into small pieces.
Cook until thoroughly heated and liquid is absorbed.
Top with cornbread batter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: colorful concoction of sautéed shapes
directions: Melt Butter in a large saute pan or wok.
Add veggies and stir fry until desired texture.
Season with Salt and Pepper.

title: spanish rice and sausage dinner
directions: In large skillet, saute peppers and onions with sausage in oil until tender. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir occasionally.

title: squash relish
directions: Chopped squash, onion and salt may be mixed and refrigerated overnight, if desired.
Then drain well and combine with other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.
(Makes nice gifts in decorative jars.)

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and fluff.
Blend in lemon juice.
Dip and enjoy!

title: corn pudding
directions: Place all ingredients together in mixing bowl and mix well. Pour into greased casserole. Bake uncovered at 360° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Bisquick, margarine, sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Batter may be a little lumpy.
Pour 2/3 of this mixture in a baking dish.
Add can of cherry pie filling on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Pour remaining batter over pie filling.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese and sour cream burritos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread tortilla with sour cream. Sprinkle with green onions, peppers and cheese.
Roll up and place in a buttered pan.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with favorite salsa when serving if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Add butter and eggs.
Stir.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Place in a buttered casserole and top with a thin layer of cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt into bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening; stir in nuts.
Pour into ungreased, square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: alphabet chicken soup
directions: In 6 to 8-quart Dutch oven, combine chicken, water, 1 tablespoon salt, peppercorns and poultry seasoning.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for one hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and peppercorns.
Skim off fat.
Cut meat from bones and return to soup.
Add alphabets, carrots, celery and onion.
Cook, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until alphabets are tender.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: breaded ranch chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the cornflakes, cheese and dressing mix. Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cornflake mixture to coat. Place chicken in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350° or until chicken juice runs clear.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Prepare 1 box of jello with this exception:
Use only 1 cup boiling water to dissolve jello, then add only 1 cup of cold water.
To this mixture, add 1/2 of the pineapple, 2 of the bananas (mashed) and 1 package thawed strawberries.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch glass dish; let set for about 1 hour, or until firm enough to layer the sour cream on top.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 9 x 12 baking pan, melt butter or margarine.
In a pan, add blackberries and sugar.
Cover with water.
Cook down on medium heat until good and hot.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven, stirring once after butter melts.

title: danish puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 3 ingredients like pie crust and mix into a ball with fork.
Divide dough into 2 portions. Spread into 2 long strips about 12 x 3 inches, 3 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: daddy's pickles
directions: Wash and put whole cucumbers into two gallon jars.
Mix spice, salt and alum into vinegar and pour over cucumbers.
Put lids on and let them set for 90 days.
Then take them out of juice and slice them as desired.
Sprinkle 8 or 9 cups of sugar to one gallon of cut up pickles.
Let stand overnight.
The sugar will draw out the juice.
Put them back in jars.
They do not have to be sealed.

title: overnight crunch coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Spread in greased floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: raw cranberry relish
directions: Pour jello into bowl.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved. Grind cranberries, orange and apple in meat grinder or Cuisinart. Add sugar and nuts.
Combine with jello and refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: italian sausage roll
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Fry in oil until brown.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Wash and cut peppers and onion.
Thoroughly fry in remaining oil and completely drain on paper towels.
Roll out dough on floured surface until the size of a cookie sheet.
Place cooked sausage, peppers and onions on dough.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Roll in jelly roll fashion, tucking the 2 ends.
Place on cookie sheet.
Baste top with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden.

title: candy delight
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until forms a soft ball. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Spread in pan to cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together; refrigerate overnight.
(If it tastes too much like onion, add a little sugar.)

title: wild rice turkey dish
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Blend in soup; add the next 6 ingredients and 1 cup water.
Mix well.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Peel and cut apples into pieces.
Place in 9-inch ungreased pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni and add vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, dressing, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni and mix.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients.
Spread the salad dressing over top. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Prepare pudding as per package instructions.
Remove from heat and stir in dry cake mix.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle top with chips and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Blend stewed tomatoes lightly in a blender (few seconds). Combine all ingredients; add stewed tomatoes.
Shape into loaf. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix other ingredients in order given in medium-sized casserole.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Sprinkle with grated cheese if you want to and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Pour 1/4 cup melted butter in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Toss cooked thin spaghetti with butter.
Cover with tomato sauce.

Add in order: 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, 1/2 package pepperoni, 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms, basil, oregano, 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, 1/2 package pepperoni and 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat just until combined.
Stir in syrup, then flour.
Stir in walnuts. Turn into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour Quick Chocolate Glaze atop.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Makes 32.

title: baklava
directions: *Use ten sheets for top and bottom layer and 6 to 10 sheets between layers.

title: carrot-raisin bread
directions: Combine sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices. Add other ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Place batter in a 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Toothpick should come out clean.

title: baked brie
directions: Roll 1/2 of dough and pinch seams together.
Slice Brie in 1/2 horizontally.
Place bottom half on crescent dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 brown sugar over Brie.
Place other half of Brie on top.
Sprinkle brown sugar and raisins on top.
Cover with remaining crescent dough and seal edges.
Place on jelly roll pan with sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: faye's wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Brown and crumble sausage.
Drain sausage well.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a casserole dish for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, eggs, crumbs, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion, salt and oregano.
Shape into a loaf and place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until no pink remains; drain.

title: cheese topped pineapple cake
directions: Cream together 1 1/2 packages of cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Gradually add 1 egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread mixture evenly in greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Blend cake mix with remaining cream cheese, eggs and water.
Beat 4 minutes and spread over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
Cut and serve with strawberries on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain well.
Stir in rest of ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Top each serving with crushed tortilla chips and grated Cheddar cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar.
Add salt.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water; stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add egg.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board; knead.
Place in greased bowl; let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Roll into a rectangle (8 x 10 inches wide).
Spread with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll, jelly roll fashion.
Place in greased pan; let rise. Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake just like regular cornbread.
Goes great with the Beef-n-noodles and the linguini.

title: chicken-vegetable soup(you can freeze in quart containers; defrost when needed.)
directions: In pot, saute onion until limp.
Combine water, bouillon, tomatoes, basil, paprika and garlic.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, zucchini and chicken. Simmer 8 minutes, uncovered.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat again until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture and then alternate with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites and pour into three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: noodle casserole(serves 4)
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with warm water.
Put noodles in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish and soups (one at a time) and stir to cover noodles.
Add 1/2 cup water. Stir well. Sprinkle cheese over top, spreading evenly. Do not cover casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: cheesy grill
directions: Thank God for dirty dishes

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine the egg yolks, flour, salt and pepper in a medium size mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites into the yolk mixture.
In a deep skillet, melt the lard to a depth of 3-inches and heat it until it registers a temperature of 365° on a deep fat thermometer.
Drop the fritter batter into the fat by teaspoonfuls, making them all nearly the same shape and size.
Fry until golden brown, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain well.
Serve immediately. Makes 18 fritters.

title: ground beef and soup casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly; add onions and celery, frying until lightly transparent.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cook in 350° oven for 1/2 hour uncovered; turn heat down to 300° and put either French fried onions or potato chips or chow mein noodles on top of casserole and cook for 1/2 hour longer.
Leave for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixer bowl (mix a little to make sure it is stirred) at slow speed.
Then add all the rest of ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Grease and flour loaf pans, filling a little over half.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Peel and cube potatoes. Cook, covered, in boiling water until tender. Drain. Reserve 2/3 cup of cooking water. Mash potatoes and set aside (should be 2 cups). Combine flour, soda and spices in an extra large mixing bowl. Set aside. Combine eggs, oil, sugar, sweet potatoes and water in another mixing bowl. Stir into flour mixture until well combined. Stir in pecans. Divide mixture evenly among three greased 8 x 4 x 2 or 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Cover with foil the last 10 minutes to prevent over-browning. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely. Wrap and store overnight before serving. Makes 3 loaves.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until brown 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut in 1-inch to 2-inch squares.
Can be made ahead and heated in microwave or frozen and served later.

title: edam cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cheese, celery, mustard and light cream.
Mix well.
Form cheese mixture into about 16 small balls and roll in parsley.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs; sift and add dry ingredients, then add vanilla, chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields 4 or 5 dozen.

title: overnight dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and Crisco.
Set aside.
Dissolve the yeast in water with sugar.
Let rise.
Mix warm milk, eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir and add to flour mixture.
Refrigerate overnight in a large greased sealed bowl.
Remove next day and use for sweet rolls, dumplings, hard rolls, kuchen or deep fried bread.
This dough can be kept refrigerated for 8 days.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Mix Italian dressing as directed on package and combine with pasta while hot.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
May be served immediately, but best if refrigerated overnight.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: In a
large kettle cover the cut up chicken with water; add salt
and
pepper.
Cook
until
tender.
Remove
chicken, strain broth and remove excess fat, if desired.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 6 to 24 hours.
Garnish with mandarin oranges and maraschino cherries.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, cook broccoli for 10 minutes in salted water, drain and place in lightly buttered casserole dish.
Pour rice over broccoli as it is (do not cook).
Mix soup mix and onion.
Pour over rice and broccoli, spoon Cheese Whiz over top and bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate kahlua trifle
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on package.
Mix pudding and set aside.
When cake is cool, slice into cubes.
Place 1/2 in glass torte dish, then drizzle 1/2 Kahlua over cake, add 1/2 pudding mix, 1/2 crushed Heath bars and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers and refrigerate overnight.

title: crescent roll coffee cake
directions: Spread one tube of crescent rolls in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until creamy and spread over the layer in pan.
Spread other package of rolls on top of cream cheese.
Beat egg white until frothy and brush on top of roll layer.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle on top of egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: easy turkey chili
directions: Brown ground turkey in large skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce, cayenne pepper and water. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally and adding water as needed.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
May add 1/4 cup masa corn mix mixed with a small amount of hot water and 2 cups chili beans.

title: sweet potato pie with caramel nut topping
directions: Mix all ingredients together until mixture is smooth.
Pour into unbaked Cream Cheese Crust and bake for 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Remove from oven and top with Caramel Nut Topping and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Mix in order given and drop teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties.
Melt fat.
Brown patties.
Mix together in a bowl tomato sauce, onion, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Pour fat off meat.
Add tomato mixture to patties; cook slowly for 10 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix dry and liquid ingredients separately. Grease only bottoms of muffin cups (24).
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, stir in oil and milk.
Pour into center of well.
Stir ONLY until flour mixture is moist.
Batter will be rough looking. Gently add berries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24.

title: fish florentine
directions: In bottom of buttered casserole, put thawed spinach, salt and pepper.
Top with fish fillets.
Saute in 1 tbsp. butter the mushrooms and the onion.
Put this over fish.
Make a white sauce of butter, milk, flour and white wine.
When thick, add the Parmesan cheese.
Pour over fish and bake at 375° for 20-25 mins.

title: hot hamburger and tostitos dip
directions: Mix ground chuck, taco mix and beans and put in an 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Top with green chilies and sour cream that have been mixed in blender.
When ready to serve, top with 8 ounce package of shredded Cheddar cheese and heat until bubbly.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: beet pickle
directions: Boil ingredients together.
Have cooked beets peeled and ready to simmer in pickling mixture 15 minutes, then seal in sterile jars.

title: miso shiru
directions: Make soup stock by boiling water and shrimp (or meat) for about 30 minutes; strain.
Add miso, tofu and green onions; cook for about 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: upside down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 2 items together and put in a greased (9 x 13-inch) cake pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour batter on top of the coconut-pecan mixture in pan.
Mix margarine and cream cheese, heat until mixture is mixed thoroughly. Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar.
Stir until dissolved and mixed.
Pour on top of mixture in pan and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix melted oleo, Karo syrup and brown sugar.
Put in microwave until it boils.
Let boil for two more minutes.
Pour over popped popcorn (in brown bag).
Shake well and put into microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and shake well.
Turn bag over and put back into microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out and spread on cookie sheets until it cools.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and drop in spoon size bits into boiling chicken broth.
Lower temperature and cover.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin impossible
directions: Mix
for 5 minutes.
Grease pan good.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: butternut squash with apples and maple syrup(serves large group - about 20)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Stir butter, syrup and apple juice in small saucepan on medium-low heat until butter melts. Increase heat and boil about 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Whisk in cinnamon, allspice and salt. Arrange 1/3 of squash in dish; top with 1/2 of apple slices. Add another 1/3 of squash. Arrange remaining squash and apples on top. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Cover tightly with foil. Bake about 50 minutes or until squash is almost tender. Uncover and bake until tender, basting with syrup, about 20 minutes. Spoon syrup over mixture and serve.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Whip cool whip and cream cheese until well blended. Add drained fruit and marshmallows. (I use colored marshmallows.) Fold in nuts and blend well. Refrigerate.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, seasonings and rice. Shape into 6 loosely formed balls. Steam the cabbage leaves until tender. Wrap each meat roll in a cabbage leaf. Place rolls in a greased skillet and add tomato juice. Cover tightly and cook on high heat until steaming. Then turn to very low heat to complete cooking. Cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, salt, margarine and Crisco well.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together 3 or 4 times.
Gradually add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in large tube pan.

title: lemony light cooler
directions: Combine grape juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Just before serving, add soda and fruit in individual glasses over ice.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add coconut. Roll nuts, dates and candy (cut up) in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Add to batter. Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted 1/2 cup margarine and graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs at high speed about 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, 3/4 cup soft margarine and vanilla; beat 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: raspberry vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate in a container with a tight fitting lid.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges in food processor. Place in large mixing bowl.
Add pineapple, nuts and sugar.
Mix together. Let stand overnight.
Excess can be frozen.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Top with cooked and sliced chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine 2 soups, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and additional cheese if desired.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut, noodles, onions and corn beef.
Mix Miracle Whip, mustard and cheese.
Spread evenly over beef.
Pour soup over all, mix lightly.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.

title: meat loaf preston
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and form loaf or loaves. Bake in 2 inch baking pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool for 15 minutes and then enjoy.
Makes 6 (4 ounce) servings.

title: linguine with prosciuitto and olives
directions: Cook linguine al dente.
Drain well and transfer to a warm serving bowl.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with vegetable tray, corn chips, etc.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, egg, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Shape into small balls and brown in skillet.
Put barbecue sauce and 1 bottle of water into crock-pot.
Drain meatballs on paper towel, then put into crock-pot.
Cook on high 2 hours or on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat
shortening,
sugar
and eggs together.
Add milk, coconut and
flour mixed with baking powder and pinch of salt. Beat just
until
mixed all together.
Add vanilla and coconut flavoring.	Pour
batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch pan.
Start cake
in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 25 minutes.
Wait
minutes	before taking out of pan.
Then cover cake while still hot.
This is a very good moist cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Arrange thinly sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in small baking dish.
Mix milk, butter, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together.
Pour over fruit. Over top of batter sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar, then pour 1/2 cup of hot water over the top.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: city scrapple
directions: Brown sausage, crumbling while cooking.
Drain well, reserving the fat for frying the scrapple.
Combine cornmeal and cold stock in a large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, or until thick.
Cover and place in a pan of simmering water for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Uncover cornmeal and return to direct heat, cooking until very thick, stirring all the while.
Meal is done when it holds its shape in a spoon.
Stir in salt, pepper, sage and sausage.
Remove from heat and add 2 eggs, one at a time.
Mix well and pack into a greased loaf pan.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour. Cool slightly and cover with another pan weighted with 3 pound weight.
(Canned goods work well.)
Cool while weighted. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice scrapple when ready to fry.
Mix remaining egg and a little water with a fork.
Dip slices in egg and then in cornmeal and fry in reserved fat.
Serve with syrup. Makes 10 to 12 slices.
Scrapple keeps 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: crepes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Stir in flour and salt.
Mix well. Refrigerate batter 1 hour to allow flour particles to swell and soften.
Pour 1/8 cup in 6-inch crepe pan or nonstick pan. Quickly tilt pan in all directions so batter covers pan in a thin film.
Flip the crepe when it shakes loose from the pan.
Cook 30 seconds.
This side will only be spotted brown.
This is the side used for the filling.
When cooked, place on a towel to cool. Stack between layers of paper towels or wax paper.
Freeze leftover crepes.

title: seafood lasagne
directions: Heat oil in medium skillet, add leek and saute until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes and paste.
Cook, stirring and breaking tomatoes with the side of the spoon until mixture boils.
Simmer, uncovered, until the sauce is slightly thickened (about 20 minutes).
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in shrimp, scallops and fish; add a few pieces of the basil leaves.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Do not boil or overcook.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put rice.
Mix soups and water.
Pour over rice.
Layer chicken parts on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with foil.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute the onion in melted butter until tender or brown.
Add thawed broccoli to onion.
Cook for a couple of minutes. Add soup. Stir together and let cook slowly for a few minutes. Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir in well until melted and mixed thoroughly. Add cooked rice. Stir and put into casserole dish.
Place in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly or browned.

title: five-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream softened butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Early in the day, cook carrots, covered in water, until barely tender; drain.
Meanwhile, gently cook onion in butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mustard, then milk.
Cook, stirring.
Add salt.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix the cookie ingredients together; roll out.
Cut and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with filling and an additional cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 - 14 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Measure margarine, dates, cherries and sugar into medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes soft paste.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts; mix.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Shape into balls.
Let stand until cool.
Yields approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: wassail bowl
directions: In a large kettle, combine cider, brown sugar, undiluted orange juice and undiluted lemonade.
Tie cloves and allspice in a piece of cheesecloth.
Add to cider along with nutmeg.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove and discard cheesecloth bag.
Stick a cinnamon stick in each serving cup.
Makes 24 servings.

title: pork chops and wild rice
directions: Flour, salt and pepper pork chops and brown on both sides very quickly in skillet.
Lay chops aside.
In 9 X 13 baking dish, pour uncooked rice into bottom of pan.
Sprinkle seasoning packet from rice box over rice.
Lay chops over the top of the seasonings.
Mix soups with water, and pour over the top of the chops.
Bake in 450 degree oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and cut into small pieces and place in bottom of a greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and pour over mixture.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Mix together and pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate  chip cookies(barbara bush - former first lady's)
directions: Blend butter, white sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken dinner casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and brown in Wesson oil in skillet. Add onion and saute. Stir in tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and rice. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Add peas and olives. Continue cooking, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: white flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add shortening and mix thoroughly.
Add water and mix well.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup milk; mix until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup more milk.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until thick. Cool and pour into crust.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown meat, drain and add all the other ingredients.
Cook until hot and it is ready to serve.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add chocolate and vanilla. Add three eggs, one at a time, beating five minutes after each addition. Pour into cooked pie shell and chill in refrigerator for several hours. Top with whipped cream and chopped walnuts.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a medium sauce pan. Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Prepare chickens and place in browning bag or crock pot.
Pour mixture over chicken. Marinate up to 24 hours for better flavor.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hour or 5 to 7 hours in the crock pot.

title: busy day beef stew
directions: In bottom of crock-pot, layer potatoes, carrots and finally meat.
Sprinkle meat with soy sauce, salt, pepper, paprika, garlic powder and flour.
Spread onions on top.
Combine beef broth, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over all.
Cook on high for 5 hours, medium for 7 hours and low for 9 to 11 hours.

title: veggie spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Combine vegetables and mix well with cream cheese. Chill several hours.
Serve party bread rounds or celery stalks. Also makes a veggie spread for bagels.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in double boiler.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, butter and 3/4 cup coconut.
Pour into cooled pie shell and cool. Top with Cool Whip and remaining coconut.

title: penuche icing
directions: Put on low flame until blended; turn flame up and boil 1 minute.
Take off heat and beat until cool enough to spread on cake.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Frosts a 2-layer cake or sheet cake.
Very good with yellow cake mix.

title: coconut or banana cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch, salt, milk and egg yolks.
Cook in microwave until thick, about 8 minutes, on High.
Add oleo and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add coconut or bananas.
Put in cooked pie shell.

title: ski tea
directions: In a large pot, bring water to a boil.

Tie spices in a cheesecloth with a string. Add the spice bag to the water. Add the tea bags and let steep for 3 minutes. Remove the tea bags. Add the juice of the oranges and lemons. Add sugar. Mix well. Serve hot in a punch bowl.

title: golden cream (potato) soup
directions: Combine potato, water, celery, carrot, onion, parsley, seasonings and bouillon. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Gradually add flour mixture to hot vegetables, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens. Add process cheese cubes. Stir until melted. Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: cashew nut loaf
directions: Saute onion in 2 teaspoons oil and 2 tablespoons water.
Put onions in mixing bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Place in oiled casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked shell.
Bake 1 hour or until center is done.

title: baked chicken packs
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Tear out four sheets of aluminum foil and set side by side.
On each sheet of aluminum foil place a sliced red potato.
Divide green pepper, red onion and tomato in four parts and place on top of potatoes.
Place a chicken breast on each pouch and season with spices to taste. Pour 1 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce over each packet.
Pour 1 Tbsp. honey over each packet.

title: rcumptous roast
directions: Score roast in several places; rub with salt and pepper. Brown on each side in oil.
Drain excess fat from roast and place in foil-lined baking dish.
Pour Coca-Cola and catsup over roast. Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.

title: (a.u.c.) carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, soda, cinnamon and salt and mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Layer in casserole dish.
Add evaporated milk, enough to almost cover potatoes.
Cover top with grated Velveeta cheese.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Check often.
Serves 6.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Combine bread crumbs, onion, egg and seasonings; mix well.
Add milk and oysters, mix thoroughly.
Spread dressing in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Pour drippings over dressing; dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with turkey.
Makes 10 servings.

title: always perfect peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter in a regular pot (do not use nonstick) and stir in sugar and cream.
Stir continuously on medium heat until you cannot keep the boil down, then stir for 8 minutes only and put peanut butter and marshmallow cream in as fast as possible.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan sprayed with pam cooking spray.

title: green punch
directions: Mix everything together in a large container, except the ginger ale.
Save it for the last ingredient, then refrigerate.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Simmer until thoroughly heated.
Serve.
Top with Cheddar cheese and sour cream.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, using only 1/2 stick melted butter.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take 2 cups crumbled cornflakes and other 1/2 butter and mix together; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pear cobbler
directions: Cut shortening into flour, add milk and roll dough out. Sprinkle pears onto dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up
into a roll like a jelly roll and slice.
Melt margarine in an oblong pan; place slices in butter.
Bring to boil sugar and water.
Pour over dough mixture.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on cookie or pizza sheet.
Press seams together to form crust.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine fat, beef and onion; cook gently for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook gently for 2 hours.
I use my slow cooker or can be cooked on stove or in oven.
Add vegetables (carrots, potatoes, celery, peas or whatever you like).
Simmer for 30 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Thicken gravy with 1/2 cup cold water and 1/4 cup flour.
Stir in gravy and cook slowly.

title: cheese quiche
directions: Saute sliced onions until clear, but not brown.
Place onions in bottom of pie shells.
Cover each with 1 package cheese.
In another bowl, mix milk, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and eggs.
Pour over cheese, dividing mixture evenly.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick. Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until firm.
Combine cool whip and condensed milk and add to pudding.
Cut up bananas and mix with all.
Place wafers along the side and bottom of dish.
Pour mixture over wafers.
Place remaining wafers on the side and across the top.
Put in refrigerator and cool.

title: pork chops
directions: Cut grooves in chops and place in milk for 30 minutes. Remove, then salt and pepper to taste.
Batter in flour and cook in electric frying pan in Crisco on medium heat until brown on both sides.

title: chicken muriel
directions: Cut up frying chicken.
Marinate in a mixture of 2 cups milk (or enough to almost cover chicken pieces) and 1 teaspoon salt for about 2 hours.
Drain, but save 1/2 cup of the marinade.
Brown chicken lightly in 1/4 cup butter.
Squeeze lime or lemon juice lightly over top.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: preacher cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water or steam if fresh; drain.
Combine veggies, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together.
Pour over veggies.
Toss gently.
Chill. Serves 4.

title: divinity candy
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Boil sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball stage when tested in cold water.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat until light, pour on buttered plate by spoonfuls.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, mashed potatoes and chocolate.
Beat well.
Add flour, alternating with buttermilk. Add nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into two greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with Coconut-Walnut Frosting.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Separate eggs; combine yolks and milk.
Blend liquid with dry ingredients.
Stir in melted shortening.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in batter.
You can use this as pancake batter also.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Layer bread in loaf pan.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper, then put over bread.
Cover with cooked, cubed chicken, eggs, milk and seasoning.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours. Just before baking, cover with soup, sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Crumbled potato chips, cornflakes or bread crumbs may be added last 15 minutes of baking.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and toss gently but mix well and chill overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into pieces and cook until done.
Mix salad dressing, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Combine with other ingredients.
Marinate several hours or overnight.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together cranberries (crush in food processor or blender), pineapple and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add marshmallows, whipping cream and nuts.
Mix well and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Before serving let set at room temperature 15 minutes, cut into squares and serve as side dish or salad.

title: brown sugar pudding
directions: Mix in baking dish the brown sugar and warm water.
Pour remaining ingredients over and bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, cornstarch and spices.
Add pumpkin. Cook about 10 minutes more.
Pour mixture into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° until pie shell is done.

title: popcorn balls
directions: In top of double boiler, melt margarine and marshmallows (or in microwave oven).
Pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Make into balls.

title: mrs. buel's recipe for spicing sweet apples
directions: Put all together and boil until soft.
Then skim out and boil down the syrup until thick.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: golden fry batter
directions: Stir Mazola oil into flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add eggs to milk and add all at once to Mazola mixture.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Prepare food to be fried by dusting with flour, then dip in batter to coat entire food.
Lift out with fork and drain off excess batter. Lower into heated oil or shortening.
Fry until food is tender and brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: *Use 1/2 eggshell to measure milk.

title: pinch bread
directions: Dissolve 2 packages dry yeast in 1 cup warm water; set aside. In large bowl pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 cup Crisco; dissolve. Add 3/4 cup sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoon salt, 2 beaten eggs, and 6 cups plain flour.
Stir.
Add dissolved yeast mixture and mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Take dough out and use 1/2 (one loaf).
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Do not knead.
Cut with small biscuit cutter.
Melt 1 stick butter and dip biscuits.
Lay biscuits in layers in Bundt pan with 1/2 full.
Cover with a towel and let rise 3 hours.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve right side up.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Cut in Crisco.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with the buttermilk to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Place on floured surface and roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each biscuit in melted oleo and fold in half.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes.
Uncooked biscuits may be frozen and used as needed.

title: puffed wheat squares
directions: Combine all ingredients (excluding puffed wheat) in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil until soft ball stage. (Mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into small dish of cold water.)
Remove from heat.
Pour over puffed wheat and mix until puffed wheat is coated.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan and press down.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: raisin tarts
directions: You will need muffin tins for this recipe.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda together.
Add mayonnaise, hot water and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed; remove out of oven. Jab holes in cake with fork. Pour cream of coconut over cake. Let cake cool. Add Cool Whip. Top with coconut. Refrigerate before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add juice to pudding; mix well.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and topping.
Add coconut and nuts.

title: no beat popovers
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add flour, milk and salt.
Mix well with spoon.
Disregard the lumps.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Put popovers in cold oven.
Set control at 450°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Don't peek!
Serves 6.

title: confetti fruit salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; toss gently. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: apple (or pear) pie in a jar
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large saucepan, heat until bubbly. Add lemon juice. Place fruit in quart jars, leaving 1-1/2 inch head space at top. Pour the hot syrup over fruit, seal. Process in hot water bath for 25 minutes, or pressure cooker for 10 minutes at 10 pounds of pressure.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well with the brown sugar.
Trim crust off bread and arrange in baking pan 2 pieces thick.

title: everlasting cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil for 3 minutes. Immediately pour over vegetables and mix well.
Refrigerate and mix from time to time.
This slaw can be made ahead and will last for weeks in the refrigerator.

title: hummus(middle eastern spread)
directions: In an electric blender, whirl together the tahini, lemon juice, olive oil, garlic salt and pepper until smooth.
With blender running, tip center cap in the cover and gradually add the chickpeas, blending until smooth and a pale color.
Stop blender as necessary and, with a rubber spatula, push the mixture towards the blades, to make sure all the chickpeas are crushed.
Chill, tightly covered.
Serve as a spread with crackers or small wedges of hot pita.
Makes a generous 2 cups.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 3 quart saucepan at medium high heat. Drain fat.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, and broth or water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Add kidney beans and simmer for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and ham.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in pan. Saute cabbage and carrots for a moment, add salt, sugar and water, cover with lid; cook 2 minutes.
Make scrambled eggs.
Place 2 tablespoons filling (cabbage, carrots, ham and eggs) on egg roll wrapper, fold up and deep fry at 400° for 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; blend thoroughly with mixer. Set aside.
Peel the apples; slice into bite size pieces.
Combine apples with cinnamon and sugar.
Layer cake batter and apple mixture in greased tube pan, beginning and ending with cake mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours, or until top is crusty and brown.
Delicious served warm with ice cream.

title: bread
directions: Combine warm water and yeast.
Add all other ingredients to yeast mixture.
Knead until not sticky.
Brush with oil.
Cover and let stand until double in size.
Punch down, knead and divide into 3 loaves.
Put into pans.
Brush with oil.
Cover and let stand; let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Butter top of loaves after baking.
(May be made into rolls instead of loaves.)

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10 cup 10-inch tube pan.
In sifter, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Alternately beat in flour mixture in fourths and milk in thirds, beginning with flour.
Beat in grated chocolate and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Dust with sugar.

title: raisin sandwich filling
directions: Beat egg slightly and add lemon and sugar.
Cook, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Add mayonnaise, raisins and nuts.
Let cool until thick.
Add butter.
Keeps well in refrigerator for weeks.

title: raspberry green beans(servings:  4)
directions: Blanch the green beans in boiling water in a saucepan for 2 to 3 minutes or until the beans are bright green.
Drain and pat dry. Melt the butter in a saucepan over medium-low heat.
Stir in the raspberry and rice vinegars and the green beans.
Cook for two minutes over medium heat.
Add the almonds; toss lightly to mix. Serve immediately.
For a special touch, add a few fresh raspberries to each plate.
Can be eaten by persons on low sodium diets.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Mix chicken, stuffing and mayo.
Stuff jumbo shells with this mixture.
Place shells that are stuffed in 9 x 13-inch pan with small amount of soup on bottom of pan to prevent sticking.
Pour remainder of soup over stuffed shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and bake for additional 15 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham in deep pan and cover with 7-Up.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cream together brown sugar and pineapple juice.
Pour off 7-Up and cover ham with brown sugar and pineapple juice mixture.
Place rings and raisins on top.
Cover and return to oven for approximately another hour.

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift together meal and salt.
Pour boiling water over cornmeal.
Add milk immediately to prevent meal from lumping. Pour into well-greased and floured muffin pan.
Bake at 475° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let sit in refrigerator until mixture thickens.
Stir in remaining ingredients and place in mold.
Return to refrigerator to chill and congeal.

title: mango cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, cook ground meat, green pepper and onion with chili powder and pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to separate meat.
Add tomato juice and beans; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 cups or 6 servings.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer the first 4 ingredients in order given.
Do not stir.
Combine the water, oleo and extract and pour over the layers in pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until light brown.
If desired, serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: swedish butter strips
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and salt.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Shape into 12-inch logs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork to 1/4-inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or brown on edges.
Cool a few minutes, then cut with sharp knife in diagonal slices.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Add graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Press mixture into greased oblong baking dish until smooth.
Spread topping evenly and quickly.
When cool, cut into small squares and enjoy like candy.

title: puppy chow snack mix
directions: Melt the peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips, stirring constantly.
Pour over cereal and mix.
Pour confectioners sugar over cereal and mix.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in water with bouillon cubes or broth and water. Remove when cooked and shred; put aside.
Cook mixed vegetables, onion and seasonings, adding rice just before vegetables are cooked.
Then add soups and chicken.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove bay leaves.
Serve.

title: banana split salad
directions: In small bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat Ricotta about 3 minutes or until fluffy.
Blend in sugar and spices. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to allow flavors to blend.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cape may seafood stew
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and red pepper.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, wine and bay leaf.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add seafood.
Cover and simmer until clams and mussels open (about 5 minutes for shells to open). Season with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate on chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the sugar, butter, cornstarch, eggs and vanilla.

Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour the mixture into the pie crust (may substitute regular pie crust). Bake for about 40 minutes or until filling begins to pull away from the sides of the crust.
Cool.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and water; mix well.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Fold in dates, nuts and cherries, one at a time, stirring well after each.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: polish noodles
directions: Chop onion and Polish sausage, saute in olive oil.
Mix with cooked egg noodles.
Let rest 5 minutes to season all flavors. Serve warm.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, butter and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter in pan, then pour hot water over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mom's hot macaroni
directions: Brown well onion and sausage.
Cook macaroni until fairly tender.
Mix all ingredients.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: italian wedding chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan; brush with garlic salt and paprika.
Mix remaining ingredients together and cover chicken. Crush bay leaves and place around chicken.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Bake 1/2 hour longer uncovered.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Roll out thin, the thinner the better.
Cut with pizza cutter.
Let dry.
Cook in hot chicken soup.
A can of cream of chicken soup makes richer.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: In heavy pan, saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Add crawfish; saute until done.
Add milk and mushroom soup.
Bring to a low boil; reduce heat and add cheese (cubed).
Season well and simmer 20 minutes.
Add fettuccine; toss and serve.
Can be served with green salad and hot rolls or garlic bread.

title: feta cheese triangles
directions: Mash Feta cheese with a fork.
Add egg yolks, egg, parsley and pepper.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Keep warm, but do not allow to brown.

title: garlic-parmesan bread
directions: Mix olive oil, oregano, garlic and water.
Spread on French bread and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: (A little baking soda added to water the beans are soaking in will de-gas.)
Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients in soup pot. Bring to a boil.
Simmer until beans are tender and desired thickness, at least 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cream all ingredients, except marshmallow cream and peanut butter, together and cook 5 or 6 minutes. Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter and mix well. Let cool; slice and enjoy!

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain and put into 8 x 8-inch greased pan or casserole dish you wish to serve in.
Arrange artichoke hearts on top of spinach.
Pour melted butter over all.
Add cream cheese, which has been softened and beaten until smooth.
Put on top.
Make sure everything is covered.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese lightly over the top of all the casserole.
Bake in oven 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Combine onion and sherry.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Combine cream cheese with beef, olives and onion.
Shape into ball and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Serve with crackers, like Triscuits or Wheat Thins.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together.
Mix jello with water; let jell
little.
Roll graham crackers; mix with some margarine and press
in 9 x 13-inch pan.	Whip cream and add jello and
cheese mixture.
Then
add
well drained pineapple.
Put this in pan and set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken adobo
directions: In large kettle, boil whole chicken with all ingredients, except cornstarch.
Cook until chicken is ready to fall apart. Remove chicken from kettle and set on paper towels to cool.
When chicken is cool, skin and bone, then cut meat into bite size pieces.
Return meat to kettle.
Add cornstarch to thicken and continue cooking for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice.
(You can add more soy sauce and vinegar to taste.)
Serves 8 to 10.

title: swiss chocolate candy bar cake
directions: Bake in layers as directed on cake mix.
Cool.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: cajun boiled shrimp
directions: Fill a large pot 1/2 to 2/3 full of water.
Start water heating.
Put the corn-on-the-cob and potatoes in hot water and cook until almost done.
Bring water to a boil.
Add onion, lemon, seafood boil and cayenne pepper.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Put cranberries, sugar and water in pan on top of stove and boil until berries pop open. Mix in jello and chopped nuts. Put in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter well.
Mix flour, lemon juice, buttermilk and soda well. Combine the two mixtures.
Oil tube pan. Spread 1 cup pecans on bottom of pan.
Pour in batter and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Layer in baking dish with crust.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: portsmouth frosting
directions: Sift flour.
Put cream in bowl and beat in sugar, a little at a time, until frosting is thick enough to spread.
Keep smooth by blending with wooden spoon.
Add vanilla and butter and beat well.

title: kids bake 'em cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a small bowl combine flour, soda and salt.
Blend well.
In a large bowl, blend butter, sugar and honey with mixer.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and chocolate chips and blend well.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut acorn squash in half from stem to bottom.
Scoop seeds from center, making a pocket in the center.
Sprinkle with Accent, garlic powder and pepper on the inside of the pocket and put a 1/4 to 1/2-inch pat of margarine in the center.

title: my mother's date-nut cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Sift	the flour and salt into large mixing
bowl.
Roll
the
dates
and
nuts	in the flour mixture (use
your hands).	Beat egg yolks until light and add sugar. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine egg yolk mixture and date-nut
mixture.	Stir
in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites until thoroughly blended.
Pack into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together and cook on a hot griddle.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix everything (except burritos) in mixer.
Spread on tortillas, roll and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Chill and slice.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix raisins, sour cream, sugar, cinnamon and egg yolks together and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Beat egg whites to soft peak and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff; spread over filling and brown.

title: hobo supper(little individual dinners)
directions: Make hamburger patties.
You need a piece of aluminum foil for each hamburger patty.
Chop potatoes, carrots and onions (any way you prefer).
Top each hamburger patty with vegetables.
Sprinkle each dinner with spices.
Seal foil on each dinner and put in 450° oven for 45 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix pineapple, Cool Whip, lemon juice, chopped pecans and condensed milk together in large bowl.
Then pour in pie crust. You can buy crust or make it.

title: smoked salmon cracker spread
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until light and fluffy (2 to 3 minutes). Add salt, lemon juice, onion, liquid smoke and horseradish. Continue beating until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes). By hand, stir in salmon. Spoon into serving bowl. If desired, garnish with pecans and parsley. Serve with crackers. Store refrigerated.

title: play dough
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and stir over medium heat.
When a ball forms, knead until smooth.
Add coloring.
This will keep for several weeks in an airtight container.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion with sausage until brown. Drain. Add
squash, soup, margarine, crackers, egg, mayonaise, cheese and sage.
Mix all together and put in baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until done.

title: crisp cocoa cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl with wooden spoon or portable electric mixer at medium speed, cream the butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture and cereal; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes, then cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: ribbon turkey loaf
directions: Mix turkey, rice, onion, egg, bouillon and garlic powder. Spoon 1/2 the mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Top with 1 slice of cheese, vegetable, another slice of cheese and remaining turkey mixture.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spread in bottom of baking dish.

title: cabbage kielbasa soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown kielbasa slices.
Drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Set sausages aside.
Add onion and cabbage to drippings.
Cook until lightly browned (7 minutes). Add carrots and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Add sausages.
Heat thoroughly.

title: royal icing
directions: Rub sugar through sieve; add lemon juice and coloring and mix well.
Whip the whites of eggs and add gradually, working it well all the time with a wooden spoon, then beat briskly until it is a smooth paste.
This can be used for piping and all kinds of fancy decorations.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Chop 1/2 cup of Snickers miniatures. Cream together the butter, 1/4 cup of confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Slowly blend in the flour, nuts and chopped Snickers. Roll the dough into 1-1/2-inch balls. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 12-14 minutes. Remove from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes. Roll the cookies in the remaining cup of confectioners sugar, completely covering them.
Makes 25 cookies.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichoke hearts into small pieces.
Mix with mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Cool slightly.
Add peanut butter and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: aunt betty's peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter several receptacles to pour fudge into (5 or 6 square pans or 2 or 3 oblong pans or plates).
Also butter a heavy kettle to cook the fudge in.
Put sugar, milk and half the salt in large kettle.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Test for hard ball stage.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Stir well. Add remainder of salt, peanut butter and butter.
Mix well.
Add confectioners sugar and mix with a rotary mixer.
Pour into buttered pans.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Parboil beans 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: tijuana train wreck
directions: Brown meat and onions in a large pot.
When onion is soft, add rest of ingredients.
Simmer about 2 1/2 hours.
Serve in this order:
large handful of smashed Doritos, sauce, chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped onion, chopped green pepper, grated sharp Cheddar cheese and top with sour cream.
Mix well and enjoy. Sauce may be frozen.

title: ratatouille(a vegetable stew)
directions: Dice eggplant into 1-inch cubes and slice zucchini into 1/2-inch rounds.
Chop onion coarsely and cut green pepper into squares.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper until they are soft; stir in eggplant and zucchini and saute a few minutes more.
Add tomato and seasonings.
Cover and simmer gently for about 30 minutes.
Uncover and turn the heat up to evaporate some of the liquid.
We like to serve Ratatouille over rice.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Drop in eggs and mix.
Sift together salt, flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Make a small ball and flatten with fork.
Place on greased cookie sheet, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch chewy cake
directions: In top of double boiler, beat eggs; add the brown sugar and butter.
Cook over boiling water until butter is melted.
Add flour and baking powder; stir well.
Add the nuts and vanilla. Mix.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping, ice cream or caramel frosting.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar together well. Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients alternately with milk until well blended.
Place in large cake pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.
Take out and cool.
Use knife to loosen cake from sides and middle.
Sift confectioners sugar on top.
Wrap to store.

title: "lite" pineapple cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix in mixer about 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in graham cracker crust.
Let set about 30 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put bright candies on top if desired.

title: piedmontese breast of chicken
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add chicken fingers and brown about 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove chicken fingers from pan; keep warm. Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Stir bouillon and wine in skillet; blend with drippings.
Cook until liquid is reduced by half.
Place chicken fingers on a heat-proof platter; pour sauce over chicken fingers.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Heat under broiler until cheese browns, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and oil.
Add flour, salt, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add oats, soda, crumbled cornflakes, nuts and coconut.
(May also add chocolate chips, M&M's, etc. if desired.)
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
10 dozen.
May freeze.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Add all ingredients in order listed.
Turn into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tested done.
Let stand overnight before cutting.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients until thickened; add pineapple and cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Add jello, stirring well. Pour into hot clean jars and seal.
Makes 8 cups.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in saucepan, bringing to a slow boil. Cook until it spins a thread or 230°. Add nuts; continue to cook until nuts smell roasted or 300°. Remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and soda. Stir until blended. Pour onto 2 greased cookie sheets. Leave until completely cooled. Break into pieces.

title: hot peppermint sippers
directions: Pour milk into saucepan.
Heat until just before boiling. Using wooden spoon, stir in chocolate sauce.
Pour hot chocolate into 2 mugs.
Add the whipped cream.
Sprinkle on M&M's and put a candy cane in each mug and use it to stir.
(The candy will be add peppermint flavor.)

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except hamburger together.
Bring to a boil and simmer.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add to sauce and simmer about 30 minutes.
Use over spaghetti noodles.

title: steak and rice
directions: After preparing steak by cutting into bite size strips; brown in skillet with butter.
After steak is brown, lower heat to medium and place remaining ingredients on top of the steak in the skillet.
Allow to simmer for approximately 35 minutes or until steak is tender.
Serve over cooked Minute rice.

title: "thank you" pie
directions: Mix together flour, butter and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Set aside.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix all ingredients together. Lightly grease 8x8 baking dish.
Pour mixture into baking dish.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Slice cheese in slim, long wedges and stuff into chilies.
Mix milk and eggs together.
Dip chilies into egg mixture and roll into the flour, then brown in oil.
Place browned chilies into casserole dish and cover with enchilada sauce.
Grate extra cheese for topping and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tomato cheese pinwheels
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 c. Flour, Sugar, Yeast and Salt. Add Tomato Juice, Water and butter; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add Egg and enough remaining Flour to form a soft dough. Place in a greased bowl; turn once to grease top.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until doubled.
Punch dough down. Divide in half; fold each half into a 15 x 12 inch rectangle approximately 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into 3 inch squares.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Make 1 inch slits in each corner of each square.
Combine Cheese and chives; place 1 heaping teaspoon in the center of each square.
Bring every other corner up to center, overlapping slightly to form pinwheels; press firmly. Bake at 400 for 8 - 10 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool. Yields 40 appetizers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Have cheese and salami sliced thick and cut into squares.
Cut up peppers and tomatoes.
Cook rotini and drain.
Pour dressing over rotini and add other ingredients.
Marinate overnight, covered.
The colored rotini looks good.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
During the last few minutes, top with cheese.
Serves 12.

title: vegetable hodgepodge salad low-cal
directions: In a large bowl, combine all vegetables except parsley. In a small bowl, combine last three ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture; mix gently to combine. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Gently stir again just before serving.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Cut tomatoes.
Cook tomatoes and syrup.
Add other ingredients and cook until thick.
Put in unbaked pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add oil and beat gradually, beat in sugar and vanilla; add flour, cardamon, soda and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Batter is real stiff before adding apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sometimes, I also add a teaspoon of cinnamon.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Cook and stir over low heat until well mixed the cocoa, oil, water and corn syrup.
Remove from heat and immediately beat in the powdered sugar.
Drizzle over cake.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside. Cream shortening, sugar and egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Add the melted chocolate and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans (greased and floured) at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and put Filling between layers.

title: frozen yogurt
directions: Blend fruit and sugar in a blender until smooth.
Stir into yogurt.
Put mixture in ice cream maker and let run for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove and freeze.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger with butter.
Add onion and tomato juice. Bring to a boil, then add baked beans, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil again.
Serves 12.
(Add chili powder, salt and pepper according to taste.)

title: whole wheat and carrot pretzels
directions: Combine yeast and whole wheat flour in a large mixing bowl. Combine 2 cups of water, butter and honey in a small saucepan and heat and stir until warm (115° to 120°) and butter is almost melted.
Pour over flour mixture, add egg and grated carrots. Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat for 3 minutes at high speed.

title: carrot onion bacon bake
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Fry bacon in large frypan.
Remove bacon and cut in small pieces.
Saute onion in drippings.
Drain liquid from carrot.
Mix carrots, onions and bacon in baking dish. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Keep in oven on warm until serving time.

title: chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in bottom of a 10-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray.
Place chicken parts on top of potatoes.
Scatter onion, garlic, basil, parsley and tomatoes over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes or until potatoes and chicken are done.
Uncover pan, using tongs or a fork. Lift up pieces so that they are on top.
