Return to pan and continue baking until chicken is brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together yams, sugar, eggs, evaporated milk, coconut, 1 stick margarine and vanilla and put in baking dish.
In saucepan, heat flour, brown sugar, water, 1 stick margarine and pecans; cook until margarine and sugar are melted.
Pour over top of yam mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a small amount of boiling water until tender; drain well and mash.
Add salt and pepper.
Combine soup, pimentos, carrots, onion, sour cream and butter, blending well.

title: doris lowery's caramel popcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, Karo, salt and vanilla; boil together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda. Pour over popped corn and peanuts; stir.
Spread out in a large baking pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour onto waxed paper and cool. Break into clumps and store in an airtight container.

title: pecan pie
directions: This makes 1 pie.
It's not what is in the pie, it's the way you mix it that makes the pie good.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Pour oil over potato wedges and stir to coat.
Place wedges in casserole dish, peel side up.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: sas' goodies
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave, stirring often to keep from getting real hot.
Blend in peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in other ingredients.
Drop onto waxed paper while hot.
Work fast.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan; pour into deep dish.
In separate bowl, mix flour and sugar; add milk.
Pour in dish with butter.
"DO NOT MIX."
Pour peaches or juice into bowl.
DO NOT MIX.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/3-inch thick.
Combine egg with water. Mix crumbs, salt, pepper and thyme together well.
Dip tomato into egg and coat with crumbs.
Fry.

title: refrigerator dill and onion pickles
directions: Place sliced cucumbers and onions in quart jar.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour over pickles; put in refrigerator for 3 days.
Ready to eat.

title: my favorite pasta(yields 4 servings)
directions: Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil.
Add mushrooms and cook about 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients including clam juice and heat through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over linguini with Parmesan cheese.

title: beef and broccoli pasta salad
directions: Combine soy sauce, oil, sherry, orange peel, ginger and garlic.
Remove 2 tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons marinade; cover and refrigerate.
Pour remaining marinade over beef.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Remove beef from marinade; discard marinade. Roast at 400° to desired doneness.
Cool.
Thinly slice beef; reserve.
Cook rotini in boiling water 12 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Combine rotini, beef, broccoli, reserved marinade, dressing, soy sauce and white pepper.
Mix gently, but well.

title: raspberry parfait
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating until glossy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into serving glasses.
Serves 4.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Beat together the eggs, light cream, flour, melted margarine and spices.
Place shredded Swiss cheese, drained shrimp and drained crabmeat in layers in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with eggs and cream mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: moms rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour into greased 9 X 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle rhubarb and nuts over the cake batter.
Sprinkle the sugar on top.
Pour whipping cream over the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
This is great!

title: potatoes ala atlanta
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, butter and cheese in large bowl.
In a separate bowl, add onion to potatoes and mix together.
Mix contents of both.
Put into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the melted butter and crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken with onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in a pan.
Add flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; stir and bring to a boil.
Add chicken broth and milk; cook slowly until thickened.
Add torn up chicken.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Pour chicken mixture into pan.
Add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel pumpkin pie
directions: Fit pie crust into 9 inch pie plate.
Fold edges under and crimp.
Cook milk in a medium size heavy saucepan over medium heat, whisking constantly or for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pumpkin.
Stir in 1 cup whipping cream and next four ingredients until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° on bottom oven rack for 40 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack and chill for 8 hours.
Cook 3 tablespoons water, corn syrup and sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Pour immediately over pie and quickly spread mixture with a metal spatula.
Let stand 2 hours before serving.
Tap hard sugar toppings with back of spoon to crack.
Beat remaining whipping cream at medium speed with mixer until soft peaks form.
Serve with pie.

title: northern bean soup
directions: Cook together the beans, ham bone, onions and carrots until beans start to get tender. Then add potatoes and finish cooking.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and vinegar; cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved, until a little ball forms when dropped in cool water.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites, beating while pouring, and continue until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat vigorously until candy stiffens.
When nearly set, drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Cut the carrots into very thin slices.
Place them in small skillet and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar, water and butter.
Cover the pan and cook over medium heat, shaking the skillet occasionally.
Cook about 8 minutes until the carrots are tender, the liquid has disappeared and the carrots are slightly glazed.
Take care they do not burn.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: cajun rice delight
directions: In a large pan, combine all ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove lid and simmer for 10 minutes more.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry with paper towels.
Place chicken breasts in pan or dish that is about 2-inches deep.
Either melt margarine and brush on chicken breasts or drizzle squeeze margarine over them.
Sprinkle with minced onion (to taste) and parsley flakes.
For 8 boneless chicken breasts, pour one can beef broth and one can water over chicken.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 375°.
(For 12 to 16 chcken breasts, use 2 cans beef broth and 2 cans water).

title: orange beets
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and lemon and orange juices until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter and pour over hot sliced beets.

title: vegetarian egg rolls
directions: Place 1 tablespoon oil in frying pan on high heat.
Mix ingredients together and stir-fry for approximately 10 minutes. Drain ingredients in a colander.
Use a serving spoon to scoop vegetables onto the wonton wrappers.
Wrap as directed on package. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Put on paper towel to drain excess oil.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix in casserole dish.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream, Cheddar cheese and cream of celery soup. Pour on top of beans and corn.
Crumble Ritz crackers and cover with melted margarine.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar and milk; pour over butter.
Place peaches in batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Follow each step in order.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine pineapple, broth, peas, mushrooms, celery, onion and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into mixture.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage and drain off fat.
Cook lasagna noodles and then mix all of the ingredients together.
Spread in lasagna pan and top with Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tea puffs
directions: Blend shortening and vanilla.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar, creaming until fluffy.
Add flour and nuts gradually to shortening mixture, stirring until blended.
Shape dough into rolls 1 1/2 inches long.
Place on baking sheet; bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Roll puffs in powdered sugar while hot.

title: spam salad
directions: Mash
Spam with a potato masher.
When well mashed, add eggs and
mash.	Add
pickles,
onion, celery and seasonings, stir. Now add enough mayonnaise to make spreadable.

title: holiday party punch
directions: In punch bowl, blend undiluted limeade and lemonade and pineapple and grapefruit juices.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and ice.
Unmold ice ring on top of punch.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Save 1/2 cup Mozzarella and 1/2 cup pizza sauce for topping later.
Mix remaining cheese, pizza sauce and other ingredients.

title: foolproof caramel icing
directions: Boil together brown sugar, syrup or cream of tartar and 1/3 cup milk until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Blend Crisco with confectioners sugar and hot milk.
Pour hot syrup over confectioners sugar mixture.
Beat to a spreading consistency.

title: potato broccoli soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, combine potato slices, contents of sauce mix envelope, water, milk and chicken broth; mix well. Bring mixture to a full boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut large pieces of broccoli and add to potato mixture.
Simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Gently stir in cheese until melted and well combined.

title: orange balls
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers.
Mix the first 4 ingredients, then put in orange juice.
Roll in balls and then roll in coconut.
Put in refrigerator until you want to use them or you can freeze them.

title: orange cake
directions: Make batter as directed, except fold in 2 tablespoons grated orange rind before baking.
Bake as directed.

title: diabetic banana applesauce fruitdressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor. Process until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Serve over sliced fresh fruit.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well; let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit real good.
Mix with other ingredients real good. Chill before serving.

title: yankee chowder
directions: Put the cream of mushroom soup in a large saucepan and gradually blend in the 3 cans of water.
When all the lumps are gone and the soup is smooth, add the other 2 cans of soup and heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garlic cheese roll(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into two small rolls and roll lightly in chili powder.
Chill, slice and serve on crackers.

title: yumm biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening (marble size). Make hole in center.
Add club soda (all at once).
Mix briskly. Knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: snack stick
directions: Dice Spam and cheese.
Put Spam, cheese, black olives and green olives on sticks; repeat until filled.
No cooking, fast, easy and fun.

title: summer cold melon soup
directions: Finely chop half of cantaloupe and honeydew and set aside. Puree remaining melon in batches with orange, lime juices and honey in food processor or blender.
Pour into large bowl.
Stir in reserved melon and champagne or wine.
Cover and chill several hours.
Garnish each serving with mint leaves.

title: meat loaf
directions: Moisten stuffing mix with water. Stir in remaining ingredients and turn into a shallow baking pan.
Form into a loaf and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil breasts and save the broth.
Layer pieces of chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Spread Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix on top of mixture and pour broth over stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add marshmallows and cook over low heat until well blended.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Stir until Rice Krispies are well coated.
Press into a well-buttered pan about 9 x 13 x 1-inch in size.
Cut into pieces when cool.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all together; boil, watching that it doesn't stick.
When thick, pour into a baked pie shell.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Lay slice of Swiss cheese over each chicken breast.
Combine white wine and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Top with crushed croutons.
Pour butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: kentucky pudding pie
directions: Mix brown and white sugar, beaten eggs, stick margarine, flour and milk in pan.
Heat only until margarine has melted, stirring constantly.
Pour warm mixture in two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 375° until brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt oleo in skillet and saute onion, celery and broccoli. Combine remaining ingredients in small casserole dish and sprinkle with garlic powder to taste.
Bake until melted and bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Serve with corn nacho chips.

title: plain yellow cake
directions: Mix all together and stir until smooth.
Pour into cake pan. Bake at 350°.

title: eggless salad dressing
directions: Exchanges:
Per 2 enchiladas = 2 vegetables, 1 bread, 1 1/2 meat and 3 fat)

title: chicken asparagus pasta with lemon sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
When done, drain and keep warm.
Melt butter in a frying pan.
Add chicken and saute 5 minutes or until edges turn golden brown.
Remove chicken to a warm plate.

title: egg gravy
directions: Cover bottom of
skillet
with bacon grease, let it get hot. Add some flour
to	make paste.
Stir with fork and cook until brown.
Add water
and cook until thick.
Add milk; stir again and cook until	thick.	Add
two or three eggs; stir and cook until eggs are
done.
Season
to
taste	with
salt
and pepper.
Serve over hot biscuits for a good breakfast!

title: tortilla stackup
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter 2 (8-inch) round cake pans. Place 1 tortilla in each pan.
Combine cheeses.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup cheese over each tortilla.
Top with generous tablespoon of green onion and chilies.

Repeat until there are 4 layers in each pan. Top with fifth tortilla. (Can be stacked as much as a day ahead and baked before serving.) Bake stacks, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until tops are lightly browned.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Invert serving platter over pan.
Carefully flip and turn stackup onto platter.
Repeat with second pan.
Cut each stack into wedges. Garnish each platter with garden salsa and sour cream.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Lay in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix ketchup and 1/2 cup cola; stir until blended.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover pork chops thoroughly with cola.
Cook in oven at 350° until tender.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all together well. Using a spoon in a large bowl. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in shallow pan. Mix oatmeal, butter, brown sugar and flour together. After ingredients are mixed well, sprinkle over apples and bake until brown. Bake at 350°.

title: red beans
directions: Bring beans to a boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put lid on beans and let set for 1 hour.
Drain water.
Put in fresh water and cook for about 30 to 45 minutes after they come to a boil.
Put in chopped onion, bell pepper and chili powder.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Brown meat in bacon drippings.
Pour in beans and add garlic.
Cook on low heat until beans are done.
Season to taste.

title: inside-out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding, cake mix, chocolate chips, milk and eggs in bowl.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 cup tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with finger.
Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove to wire rack; cool completely.
Place on cake plate and dust with powdered sugar.

title: johnny mozzetti
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onions and green pepper until tender and well done.
Drain and put into a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Add soups and 1 cup cheese to meat.
Cook the noodles in boiling water until done.
Drain; add to the meat mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until cheese is golden brown.

title: corn bread with broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until brown on top.
Freezes well.

title: low fat artichoke and green chili dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise and yogurt in medium mixing bowl; stir until smooth. Add artichoke hearts, green chilis, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and hot sauce; stir well. Coat 1 quart baking dish with cooking spray; spoon in mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and broil 5 1/2 inches from heat for 1 1/2 minutes, or until lightly browned. Garnish with green chili slices, if desired. Serve with whole wheat toast points, bread sticks, unsalted crackers or melba rounds. Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, then add nuts and dates. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from the pan to a cooling rack.
Allow to cool and frost.
Makes 2 2/3 dozen bars.
These make a complete fall dessert.
They may be topped with whipped cream instead of frosting.

title: griddle cake
directions: Cut 10 to 12 circles of wax paper size of griddle.
Preheat oven and cast-iron 8-inch or 9-inch griddle to 425°.
Be very careful; griddles are always hot during this process.
Dump all ingredients together and beat on High until lumps are dissolved and batter is bubbly.
Put one sheet of wax paper in griddle and pour about 1/2 cup batter in.
Bake 3 to 8 minutes or until spongy feeling.
Do not wait for top to turn very brown.
Loosen edges from paper with spatula or case knife.
Turn that layer out onto plate and repeat.
While the next layer is coking, spread a thin layer of icing on previously cooked layer and be ready for next one.

title: gazpacho
directions: Soup:
Combine tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper, onion and garlic in a bowl.
Place 1/2 of this mixture in your electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Return to bowl; add oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Garnish with toasted bread crumbs, if desired.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix vinegar with oil, celery seed, salt, sugar and mustard. Boil for 3 minutes and pour over all.
Can cut down on oil.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add flour, baking powder and mace mixed together.
Beat well.
Beat eggs separately.
When yolks are thick and lemon colored, add sugar.
Combine mixtures.
Beat whites until stiff, then fold into other mixtures.
Pour into standard loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: meal in a pan
directions: Fry first 5 ingredients in oil and salt.
When almost done, add beaten eggs.
Fry until done.
Serve hot.

title: split pea soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown bacon; drain. Stir in onions, celery and garlic and cook until vegetables are tender. Add carrots, water, bay leaf, salt, pepper and rosemary and heat to boil. Stir in green peas and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes. Season with salt and pepper if needed. Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain cooked beans and add chicken soup.
Season to taste. Add onion soup mix and sour cream.
Cover with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: molasses rolls
directions: In saucepan, add 1/2 cup water and shortenings until melted. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to fat mixture with milk and molasses.
Stir in salt and soda; beat in gradually enough flour to make soft dough.
Let rise until doubled.
Shape into 24 balls and put into two greased 9-inch round pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Brush with a little molasses. Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fresh strawberry salad
directions: Pour the hot water over the gelatin and stir well to completely dissolve. Add 1 1/2 cups cold water. Shape cream cheese into balls (use 1 teaspoon for each).
Roll in the chopped nuts. Place cheese balls, evenly spaced, in a 9-inch ring mold.
Cover with the lightly sugared strawberries.
Pour cooled strawberry gelatin over cheese balls and berries.
Chill until the gelatin is set.
Unmold on a large serving plate. Serves 8.

title: alessandra and francesca's favorite pasta with broccoli
directions: Place oil in a saucepan.
Place on medium heat.
Add garlic. As garlic begins to become lightly browned, add broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is done.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend all the ingredients together with an electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Fill each one half full with batter.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf comes out clean.
Let cool.
Serve plain, with margarine or with cream cheese.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Microwave margarine and marshmallows on full power in large glass mixing bowl for 2 minutes.
Stir to combine.
Microwave on full power 1 1/2 to 2 minutes longer.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal; stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: texas beans
directions: Take 2 pounds of pinto beans, pick out rocks.
Take 4 loops of your favorite German sausage and cut up in large bites.
Take 2 yellow onions and cut in hunks.
Combine all 3 and simmer for 8 hours or more, until beans are tender.
Do not use other seasonings.
Use a large pot.
Add 2 cans stewed tomatoes, cut them up and add juice.
Simmer with lid off until it reaches desired consistency.
Serves 12.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in jar; cover. Store in refrigerator for 24 hours; remove garlic clove.
Serve with tortilla chips or potato chips.
Will keep refrigerated for 2 weeks.

title: brown bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place large pan of boiling water on lower rack of oven for steam.
Grease four bread pans.
Bring 3 cups of raisins to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: drip beef
directions: Simmer 8 to 24 hours on low in a crock-pot.
Shred beef with 2 forks and return to juice.
Add 1 package onion gravy or soup mix to juice.
Serve over hamburger buns or sourdough rolls with bowls of juice for drippings.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Sprinkle blueberries with lemon juice; set aside.
Combine flour, cloves, sugar, and nutmeg.
Stir well and add to berries; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Add butter (dot over top).
Cover with second unbaked pie crust.
Cut slits in top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring the first 4 ingredients to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Do not underboil or overboil. Remove from heat.
Add the last 3 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper until cool.
Makes 20 to 24 cookies.

title: herb-roasted chicken
directions: Mix lemon peel,
oregano,
sage, marjoram, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and garlic in
small
bowl.
Gently
loosen
skin
from breast and
legs of
fryer.
Rub
herb
mixture
under
skin. Replace skin.
Place onion and
bay leaf in cavity of chicken. Secure legs together with
string.
In small bowl, mix parsley and
1/8 teaspoon
pepper.	Rub
onto
chicken
skin.
Place chicken breast-side up on
roasting rack in microwave.
Microwave at High for 18 to
minutes, or until legs move freely and juices run clear, rotating rack twice.
Let chicken stand, covered, for 10 minutes before carving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Cover with celery and mushrooms.
Mix soup and cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: bread pudding
directions: You will need 1 large deep baking pan.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries to dissolve, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan and chill.
When firm, spread sour cream over top, then pour remaining Jell-O on top. Chill to firm.

title: chili blanco or white chili
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soups and water; mix well. Heat through. Add the chicken, if desired. Stir in lemon juice and pepper. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes(crock-pot)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and onion.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute only.
Layer potatoes and sauce 3 times in a crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 6 hours or on high for 4 hours.
This may be adjusted to suit your crock-pot.

title: special fried rice
directions: Bring water to boil. Add rice; reduce heat. Cover and cook over medium 15 to 18 minutes. Spread rice out on a cookie sheet to quick cool it.

title: cucumbers in sour cream(mizeria)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thin; add salt to cucumbers and let stand for 1 hour, then drain liquid.
Add sour cream, sugar, vinegar, pepper and finely chopped onions and mix thoroughly. Garnish with parsley.
Yield:
Buffet style.

title: deer steak fingers
directions: Slice meat into thin strips, about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine salt, pepper and flour in bowl.
Dip strips of meat into flour mixture.
Cooking oil should be very hot.
Drop strips into cooking oil, browning on both sides.

title: butter pecan bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat well.
Stir in the pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes (toothpick will come out clean in center when done).

title: stir-fried shrimp and pea pods
directions: Heat oil in wok or frying pan with ginger and garlic.
Add shrimp and stir-fry 1 1/2 minutes.
Add pea pods and bamboo shoots; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add chicken bouillon, soy sauce, sugar and sherry and stir-fry 2 minutes.
Serve on hot cooked rice.
Serves 2.

title: lovage spread
directions: Chop lovage and onion in food processor.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Let flavors mellow for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Use as a dip/cracker spread on a baked potato or instead of mayo on a sandwich.

title: butternut flavoring pound cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
Alternate eggs with flour.
Add salt and flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake in greased pan at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed with veggies
directions: Steam veggies together.
Place mixture of veggies and sauce in center of rolls unfolded in points, overlap.
Pull crescent points over veggies to close. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl, beating at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 layer pans (greased and floured). Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans for 15 minutes. Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and top with frosting.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Layer each of the following:
Oreo cookies (crumbled in blender), Blue Bell homemade vanilla ice cream. Hershey's chocolate syrup, whipped cream, Oreo cookies (crumbled in blender).
Spread 1st layer of Oreos on bottom of cake pan. Soften Blue Bell ice cream; spread over crumbled cookies.
Pour Hershey's over ice cream; spread evenly.
Layer whipped cream evenly over syrup.
Add top layer of crumbled cookies.
Freeze; eat and enjoy.
Brush and floss.

title: fried okra and potatoes
directions: Cut off top and and ends of the okra pods, then cut into 1/4 inch rounds while partially frozen.
Peel and dice potatoes into 1/2 inch pieces.
Peel the onion and chop finely.
Place the okra, potatoes and onions into a plastic bag and add the corn meal, salt and pepper.
Shake until well coated.
Add to a frying pan with 1/2 inch of oil.
Cook on medium until the potatoes are done and mixture is nicely brown.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients in 2 cups of chicken broth; puree.
In 1 cup chicken broth, cook potatoes, diced very small. Add curry, salt and pepper to taste.
When potatoes are tender, add the puree.
Spices may be added as desired.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Microwave squash, onion and grated carrot in an 8-inch microwave-safe pan on High, covered, for 6 to 8 minutes until tender (add a small amount of water if necessary).
Drain and add soup, eggs, cheese, margarine and seasonings.
Mix to blend. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and cook for 6 to 8 minutes on High.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs and cook 1 to 2 additional minutes, uncovered.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix together; shape into patties.
Fry in oil.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box; allow to cool completely. Crumble half of cake in a punch bowl or other large glass bowl. Layer pineapple, banana slices, strawberries and pudding.
Repeat layers and top with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: jeff's barbecue pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in large Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients, except potatoes, mix well and pour over roast.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add potatoes and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix together cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Add drained, flaked crab meat and onions.
Mix.
Turn into 8-inch greased pie tin and top with toasted, slivered almonds.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant ole
directions: Rinse eggplant, peel and cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices. Place eggplant in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish, overlapping slices as needed.
Add water.
Cover with vented microwave-safe plastic wrap or glass lid.
Cook at 100% power 7 to 9 minutes or until eggplant is tender, turning dish once.
Drain.

title: apple raisin coffee cake
directions: Spiced
Sugar:
Mix
together
1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg.

title: mamma's brown gravy
directions: Leave enough
grease
in
the skillet after frying meat (pork, beef
or
chicken) and add flour on medium-to-high heat and stir constantly with a fork until dark golden brown.
Then add water and
cook
until
it
just	will run out of a spoon. Also, leave the
crispies
in
the
grease from the fried meat because they add
a lot of rich flavor.	Salt and black pepper to taste.
Serve over hot rice, grits or mashed potatoes.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Melt together milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Mix yeast mixture and add 3 3/4 cups flour.
Let rise one hour.
Makes 18 rolls.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it forms a medium soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour 2/3 of the syrup slowly over the egg whites.
Beat constantly.
Cook remaining 1/3 of syrup mixture until it forms a very firm ball.
Beat it slowly into first mixture, beating constantly, until creamy.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Cook on low heat 12 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly, add sugar, Karo and salt, mix well. Add butter and vanilla, beat well. Put pecans in bottom of pie shell, pour mixture over nuts. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 300 degrees and cook for 35 minutes longer.

title: parmesan chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture.
Coat both sides.
Melt margarine in a baking dish in oven.
Add chicken, turning to coat both sides with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.
Exchange per 1-piece serving equals 4 lean meats.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Simmer the first 4 ingredients 15 minutes. Strain. Add the orange juice and lemon juice.
Heat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, celery, onion, Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise. Place in a casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, Blue cheese, onion, relish, Worcestershire, horseradish, mustard and salt.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Fold in the Swiss and Cheddar cheeses.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put 1 can beans in bottom of a baking dish.
Brown meat and drain; add to top of beans.
Spread sour cream on top of meat. Pour tomato sauce over sour cream.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions in butter 5 minutes. Blend in flour. Add broth. Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Cool slightly. Add cream and seasoning. Heat through. Serves 6.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Boil together water, margarine, oil and cocoa.
Pour the boiled mixture over the flour and sugar mixture, mixing well.
Mix together buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add this mixture to the flour and sugar mixture.
Pour into a greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Cook beans and onion in a large skillet while meat is browning, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain.
Stir in beans and envelope of taco seasoning mix.
Cook, uncovered, until thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat.
Stir in taco sauce and salad dressing. Cool mixture slightly.
Combine lettuce and green onion.
Place in a large bowl.
Crush chips, reserving several whole ones for garnish.
Set aside a small amount of chopped tomatoes for garnish.
Layer remaining tomatoes, meat mixture, crushed chips and cheese on lettuce.
Garnish with reserved whole chips and chopped tomatoes.
Serves 6.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine lemon jello and hot water; let set slightly, then mix in other ingredients.
Put in 8 x 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve red gelatin in boiling water.
Add red hots candies and stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce.
Chill.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease round pan.
Mix ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute oleo, onions, bell pepper, celery and Ro-Tel for about 4 hours covered.
Add juice of lemon, Worcestershire and 2 buttons of garlic.
Then add mushroom soup and shrimp.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix well.
Spread on 6 English muffins that have been cut in half.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Cut into 4 to 8 pieces to serve.
Can freeze before cooking.

title: stone soup
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until tender. Then add celery soup, Veg-All and cheese. Simmer until cheese melts.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and milk for 2 minutes. In a separate bowl, mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Swirl into cake batter. Bake at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chunk cheese and chili.
Simmer about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate "miracle whip" cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Gradually mix in Miracle Whip, water and vanilla.
Mix on
medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Excellent with peanut butter frosting!

title: classic chocolate sauce
directions: Melt baking chocolate and butter in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Stir until chocolate has melted.
Gradually stir in sugar and salt.
Add evaporated milk; blend well.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream or other dessert. Makes 2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Set aside. Add rice, soup, onions and celery. Melt butter. Soften Cheez Whiz in microwave (lid off). Add broccoli and all remaining ingredients. Spread in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (30 to 40 minutes with foil on and 10 to 15 minutes with foil off).

title: seven layer pudding
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer as follows:

title: party pate
directions: Heat consomme and add gelatin until dissolved.
Pour half into bowl or mold and refrigerate.
Beat pate and cheese with seasonings and brandy.
Press pate mixture on top of jellied consomme.
Cover with remaining consomme.
Return to refrigerator to jelly.
Unmold and garnish with chopped parsley and/or sieved egg yolk.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, milk, cornflakes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into 6 patties.
Roll in flour; brown in shortening.
Place in baking dish; cover with mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix the crushed Oreos with butter (reserve 1/4 cup crumbs for sprinkling on top).
Press crumbs in pie plate.

title: cheese-onion french bread
directions: Mix together grated cheese, mayonnaise and green onions. Spread sliced French bread with melted butter, then spread cheese mixture between slices and on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Wrap loaves in foil and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Uncover during the last 10 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs (3 whole eggs and egg yolk of fourth egg).
Add flour and salt.
Mix the milk, vinegar and baking soda well; add to cake batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan; bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Ice with Seven-Minute Icing.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef; add onion and drain grease off.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spoon beans over ground beef.
Add chopped chilies, then spread taco sauce over mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole; top with toasted slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk to a hard boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add water, dry soup or gravy mix, frozen vegetables and tomato sauce.
Simmer and season to taste.

title: elephant ears
directions: Beat eggs until very fluffy, about 8 minutes.
Beat in water and salt; stir in flour.
Knead slightly, until not sticky, but still soft.

title: spiced and sugared walnuts
directions: Place walnuts on a cookie sheet in a 325° oven.
Toast 15 minutes and cool.
Combine sugar and spices in a 2-quart pan.
Add water.
Heat to boiling with cover on.
Boil 3 to 4 minutes. Uncover and boil to soft ball stage, 236° on a candy thermometer. Add butter and orange peel.
Stir until creamy; add walnuts and stir until coated.
Turn out on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Separate as soon as you can handle nuts.

title: creole chicken and rice
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
chicken in 1 1/2 quart baking dish;
sprinkle
with
salt and pepper.
Combine rice, water, tomato sauce, green pepper, celery, onion and thyme in bowl;
mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, with foil for 1 hour.

title: crazy berry blue pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin over low heat.
In another bowl, mix milk and lemon juice.
Stir in gelatin mixture.
Now add sour cream. Fold in pie filling.
Pour into graham cracker crust and garnish with rest of pie filling.
Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 3 (1 pound) well-greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ranch olives
directions: Drain olives. Whip cream cheese, adding Miracle Whip, parsley and dressing mix.
Using a frosting pipe with a large bore tip, carefully pipe this mixture into the olive's cavity.
Serve chilled.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix cheese, oleo, pepper and flour.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with fork. Bake at 300° until light brown.
Can be doubled.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine eggs, milk and soup in bowl; mix well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Add sugar and mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread over top.
When cool cut into squares.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
Set aside.
In small deep bowl whip the cream, vanilla and sugar.
Fold whipped cream into cheese mixture.
Add cake pieces; set aside.
Combine strawberries, sugar and almond extract.
Layer in large glass bowl starting with strawberries, then adding cake mixture.
Continue layering; finish with strawberries attractively arranged on top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill well.
Serves 24.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Cook Uncle Ben's as directed on box.
In separate pan, saute margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Bottom layer, bean dip.
Next layer, mix sour cream with taco seasoning mix and spread over bean dip.
Next, spread avocado dip. Next, layer chopped black olives.
Next layer, green onions. Next layer, chopped tomatoes.
Finish off by covering the top with shredded cheese.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan and cook about 30 minutes on medium heat until desired texture.

title: malted milk drink
directions: Blend on high until creamy.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Brown meat; drain and break into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients, adding cheese last.
Cook in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
This makes a large batch.
Serve with a salad and ice tea.

title: ell's cheese ball
directions: Cheese should be at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into a large ball or 2 small balls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill and serve.
Good served with wheat crackers.

title: cake batter
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Rotate flour and milk. Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion.
Add garlic salt, black pepper, vinegar, mayonnaise and buttermilk.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: oh-so-good-cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, margarine, oil and egg.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls (be generous) onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake 5 minutes on lower rack and then 5 minutes on middle rack at 350°.

title: hamburger loaf
directions: Cut off top of bread.
Save.
Clean bread out of center, tear center bread into pieces, set aside.
Brown hamburger, add soups, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Stir.
Add bread pieces. Layer cheese in bottom of loaf.
Spoon in hamburger mixture.
Top with more cheese.
Place top back on loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and butter together in a large bowl.
Fold in whipped whipping cream.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill well (4 to 5 hours).
Serve with fudge sauce.

title: chicken balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 4 hours or overnight.
Roll into balls and roll in cracker crumbs.
Chill and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly on moderate speed.
Add vanilla, nuts (optional) and apples.
Mix. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, for 1 hour at 350°. A very good cake.

title: angel berry cake
directions: With sharp, thin-bladed knife, make slits at 1-inch intervals around top of cake, between center and rim, cutting through cake from top to bottom.
With knife, insert berries into slits. Spoon juice evenly over berries.
Whip cream with sugar, vanilla and food coloring.
Frost entire cake.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: dole honey-lime fruit toss
directions: Combine ingredients and toss with dressing.

title: green chili cheese squares
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put half of the grated cheese in bottom of pan. Sprinkle green chilies on cheese.
Cover with remaining cheese. Beat eggs and pour over cheese and chilies. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
These freeze very well and are good for breakfast or hors d'oeuvres.

title: maxcine's ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Slightly mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put the 1/2 cup of cheese on top and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
(Reserve 1/2 cup cheese for last.)

title: strawberry bermuth cake
directions: Break up angel food cake into small pieces and cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix one small package of vanilla pudding mix with one cup of milk.
Add vanilla ice cream and beat until smooth.
Pour over cake.
Dissolve strawberry jello with one cup of hot water.
Let cool slightly and add frozen strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour this over the vanilla mixture.
Lap with Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: chewy cake
directions: Bake in oven at 325° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup and water; place in pan.
Top with mixed catsup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Wash peppers, cut in half, cover with cold water.
Bring to boil.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Combine cooked meat and onion with rice, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper, catsup and 1/2 of the tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Stuff peppers.
Stand in baking dish, pour over the rest of the tomato sauce, mixed with 1/3 cup water.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water. Bring to a boil the 1 cup water.
Add the margarine and shortening.
Remove from heat and cool.
In a large bowl, mix the eggs and sugar.
Add 1 cup cold water. Combine all 3 mixtures.
To this, add the flour. Mix, cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: pane italiano
directions: Cut a thin slice of top of bread.
Hollow out inside of loaf, leaving a half-inch shell.
Brush inside of loaf lightly with olive oil.
Place on baking sheet and heat at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes until inside is dry but not browned.
In a medium saucepan, combine tomato sauce, plum tomatoes, basil, oregano, salt and bring to a bubbling state.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from burner and stir in Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon mixture into hollowed loaf and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until loaf is a golden brown and the filling is bubbly. Cut into thick slices and serve hot.
Enough for 4 generous helpings.
Ideal for lunch or supper.

title: lasagne florentine
directions: Prepare noodles.
In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Wait until tender, then add sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs in bowl until well blended.
Stir in remainder of ingredients. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.
Very easy to make!

title: fruit leathers
directions: Puree in blender the plums and applesauce.
Bring to boil with sugar.

title: indian relish
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and chop finely.

title: shake pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar with sliced cucumbers and onions, depending on your taste.
Mix together sugar, vinegar, salt, alum, celery salt, mustard seed and turmeric.
Pour mixture over the cucumbers and onions.
Place jar in refrigerator.
Shake once a day for 6 days. Ready to eat.
As you use pickles from jar, you can replace and keep jar full.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix everything except raisins and bread. Make sure it is blended well.
Add raisins and bread. Make sure all bread is soaked.
Let stand in fridge for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dump pineapple and cherry filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Evenly spread dry cake mix on top (do not mix).
Cut stick butter into pats and place on top. Bake 1 hour.
Great warm!

title: broccoli moureen
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Saute onion in butter; add broccoli, rice, soup, water, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Bake in greased casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream kuchen
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Put half the batter in a greased Bundt pan.
Combine the last 3 ingredients and sprinkle half on top of the batter. Spread on the rest of the batter, then sprinkle on the rest of the topping.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan after it has cooled for 10 minutes. When cooled, glaze with a thin powdered sugar glaze.

title: mushroom beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large casserole.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.
Great for Sunday dinner!

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and
add
powdered
sugar.
Cream
until smooth.
Add
flour,
salt,
vanilla and nuts (mixture will be stiff).
Pinch off small pieces of dough;
shape into ball and place on
ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar while still warm. Makes 4 dozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: leonard's corn bread
directions: Mix well with water.
Put in well-greased pan and bake at 400°.

title: "a little different" slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise and salt; let sit 15 minutes for seasoning to melt.
Add cabbage and allow to sit at least 30 minutes. (Adjust quantities to taste.)

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Makes about one 14 ounce can.

title: bob's homemade ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten eggs; mix well.
Make in ice cream freezer.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Crush cereal and stir in remaining margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. (If using fresh hash browns, cook few minutes longer.
Really good reheated.)

title: easy chicken-rice dinner
directions: In large skillet with cover, brown chicken strips in oil. Remove chicken and reserve.
Add onion, garlic, rice and vegetables to skillet.
Saute lightly; add water and bring to boil.
Stir well; add chicken and lower heat to simmer.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes or until done.
May add more water near end of cooking time if you prefer a more moist dish.

title: easy fudge
directions: In large saucepot, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup Eagle Brand milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Spread mixture in wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Next, melt chocolate morsel chips, remaining milk and butter.
Spread on top peanut butter mixture.
Chill 2 hours. Turn out on flat surface; peel wax paper away and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add peanut butter and cream until soft.
Add the sugar (brown and white) and vanilla, creaming.
Beat eggs; add flour, soda and salt.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage pockets
directions: In bowl, add sugar, salt and 1/2 of flour; mix well.
Use the rest of flour for kneading.
Cover with a dough cloth and let rise until double in size.
Roll out 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in squares.
Brown ground beef, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook until done.
Drain off fat.
Cook cabbage until color turns.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon mixture to each square and bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Good to serve with a cheese sauce.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: In large skillet sprayed with vegetable spray, cook onion and green pepper until onion is clear.
Remove from skillet.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chops, one at a time; shake to coat meat.
Brown chops in skillet.
Place pineapple slice on top of each chop.
Sprinkle with onion and green pepper. Combine vinegar, catsup and pineapple juice to make sauce.
Pour over chops.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chops are done.
Calories: 179 per serving.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts and remaining ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or until well chilled.
Makes 1 cheese ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: egg custard
directions: Cook for a while over low heat.
Also, cook pie shell for a while, about half done.
Pour custard into crust; cook at 350° until knife comes out clean when inserted.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheerios-molasses patties
directions: Measure Cheerios and peanuts into large greased bowl.
Mix sugar, molasses, water, vinegar and cream of tartar in saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, to hard ball stage (250°).
(A hard ball forms when a small amount of syrup is dropped into cold water.)
Remove from heat.
Blend in soda; mixture becomes fluffy and porous.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Put sugar,
flour,
soda,
salt
and
spices into large bowl; stir well
with
a
fork to mix.
Make a well in center; add nuts and
raisins
that
have been soaked in 1 cup of warm water, oil, eggs,
cup
water
(from soaked raisins) and grated sweet potatoes.
Blend
well;
pour into large greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Bake this quiche in 9-inch pie pan about 20 minutes on 400° until firm or golden brown.
Garnish with tomato slices, olives and sour cream.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions in weak salt solution 1 hour.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in jars.
Boil vinegar solution down until it fits in jars.

title: syrup cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, syrup and oil.
Mix with blender.
Then add boiling water and mix until well blended.
Pour in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: ham - jacks
directions: Split English muffins.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on muffins.
Put under the boiler and cook until bubbly brown and hot.
This will feed 3 to 6, depending on circumstances such as consumer's size, appetite and greed.

title: two bean - beef bake
directions: Cook limas until almost tender.
Drain.
Brown meat in skillet.
Add celery, peppers and onions.
Cook until well done. Stir in limas, pork and beans, tomato paste, water, chili powder and salt.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with border of chips.

title: lasagne
directions: Bring 4 to 6 quarts of water to a rapid boil.
If desired, add up to 2 teaspoons salt.
Cook noodles 12 minutes or until tender.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Grate
and salt zucchini.
Set aside for 1/2 hour.
Mix eggs, flour,
baking
powder and milk if using frozen squash. Add cheese.
Saute
onion
in bacon grease after frying bacon (pour off
some
of
grease).
Mix
all and pour into greased 9-inch pie
plate.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (no pie crust is needed).

title: chicken pie
directions: Take meat off bones; fix layer of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and broth and bring to boil.
Pour over chicken, then put Veg-All over chicken.
Make crust using rest of ingredients; mix and pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no salt herb seasoning
directions: Shake all ingredients in a glass jar.
Keep covered.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Great for all meats and poultry.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients 3 times.
In mixing bowl, add milk, stirring to make a smooth batter.
Add egg, stirring well.
Add bacon drippings; stir well.
Bake in well-greased pie pan or well-greased muffin pans at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: potatoes and cheese
directions: Heat milk, cream cheese and soup.
Pour over potatoes in a 9 X 13 pan, mixing slightly.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon muffins
directions: Cut bacon in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook bacon in saucepan until golden brown.
Pour fat through strainer over measuring cup and add vegetable oil if needed to make 1/4 cup.
Drain bacon on paper towel.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Whisk egg, milk and bacon fat in small bowl until egg is well broken up.
Add bacon and pour over dry ingredients.
Fold with rubber spatula until dry ingredients are moistened.
Scoop into pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes.
Turn onto rack.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken until meat falls apart.
Crunch up Doritos nachos and put on bottom of casserole dish.
Cut up meat and put on top of nachos.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel together and cook until warm. Pour over chicken, put slices of Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes on 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni;
drain.
Cook
ground
sausage;
drain. Grate cheese.
Preheat
oven to 450°.
Layer macaroni, sauce, sausage, olives, mushrooms and cheese.
Layer all ingredients until casserole
pan is full.
Top with cheese and bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: party punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale before serving. Makes 24 (6 ounce) servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: raspberry-applesauce mold
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candies in 2 cups boiling water.
Add jello; mix well.
Add applesauce.
Pour into mold.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on the package; drain well.
Saute onions in the margarine.
Drain and quarter artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: italian garlic bread
directions: Spread both pieces of bread with margarine.
Mix olives with garlic.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, oregano and cheese on bread.
Put
bread
back together.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream and fluff butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to sugar and butter; mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drain and chop up cherries; add to mixture.
Also, add nuts and raisins at this time.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook until mixture becomes thick and bubbly.
Then pour into bowl with bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: one loaf whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt, honey or molasses and shortening. When cool, add yeast mixture and whole wheat flour.
Beat well. Add white flour to make a stiff dough. Knead until smooth and satiny.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise.
After dough has doubled in bulk, punch it down and let rise again.
Make it into one loaf.
Let rise until double. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove. Brush with melted butter and after it has cooled, wrap in aluminum foil.
It will freeze well.

title: punch bowl cake(serves many)
directions: Cook cake according to directions.
Cube cake.
Layer 1/2 cubes in bottom of punch bowl.
Top with 1 can of cherry pie filling, 2 boxes of prepared pudding, 1/2 of pineapple, 1/2 of bananas and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat procedure.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and thick.
Add sugar.
Beat with electric mixer 2 1/2 minutes.
Fold sifted dry ingredients into egg and sugar mixture.
Melt butter in hot milk and add all at once.
The folding in of the dry ingredients and milk should take 1 minute.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
I bake mine in a greased and floured angel food cake pan.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll out thick.
May be dropped by spoonfuls (use less flour).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: muffin tin no fat biscuits
directions: Have muffin pan very hot and sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 425° until brown, approximately 30 minutes. Yields 12 biscuits.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat tomato juice and onion.
Pour over Jell-O.
Add celery, olives and vinegar.
Chill.
Good with most any meat; also for luncheon.

title: microwave garden fresh cabbage
directions: Wash and cut cabbage into uniform pieces.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave for 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Remove from microwave and add seasonings.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: williamsburg turkey rice soup
directions: Cook turkey in 4 quarts of water for 1 hour or longer. Season water with a little salt and pepper.
Remove carcass from broth and pick meat from bones.
Set broth and meat aside.
Heat butter in Dutch oven.
Add flour and cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly for 5 minutes (makes a roux that is very light in color).
Stir in chopped onion, diced carrots and celery.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add 3 quarts of chicken broth (add water, if necessary, to make 3 quarts).
Add turkey, rice, salt, and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add half and half. Cook until soup is thoroughly heated.
Yield: 4 1/2 quarts.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Night before, place potato, corn meal, soda, salt and sugar in a Pyrex dish. Pour boiling water over first 5 ingredients. Stir. Cover and put in oven with light on for 10 to 12 hours, until light and foamy.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper in large frying pan.
Pour off drippings.
Sprinkle chili powder, salt and pepper over meat.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover tightly and cook until rice is done, 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix in last 4 ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 pies.

title: pringles candy
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan over low heat.
Pour out onto foil when bark melted.
Let set until cool and break into pieces.

title: chili
directions: Brown the beef.
Drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for about 45 minutes until done or about 3 hours in a crock-pot on low heat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Combine other ingredients (except whipped cream).
Fold in whipped cream and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp con queso dip
directions: Place all ingredients, except shrimp, into top of double boiler.
When cheeses are melted and mixture is well blended, add shrimp.
Serve with large Fritos.
Freezes well.
Makes a lot.

title: crepes
directions: Add water to the flour, baking powder and salt until a soft dough.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Pour small amount in hot frying pan.
When top looks dry, turn over and cook until tan.
Batter should be spread very thin in pan.

title: best sabbath meat loaf
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 can of tomato soup, diluted with 1/2 can water.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Some people had springs on their farms, and had a spring box which was just a wooden box sitting in the spring to contain foods, such as milk, butter, meats, etc.
If a spring was not on the farm, then many households lowered a bucket into the well to water level and the food items in it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toss together chicken, rice, eggs, celery and onion.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and salt.
Add to rice mixture.
Put into buttered casserole (3-quart size or large flat baking dish).
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. Remove from refrigerator about an hour before baking.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes uncovered.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked crust.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: green chilies and chicken casserole
directions: *Optional:
Substitute nacho cheese soup for mushroom soup.

title: chocolate nut crumb cake
directions: While melting 1/3 cup of chocolate chips, grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter. Stir in pecans and 2/3 cup of chocolate chips.
Combine flour with soda and salt.
Cream the butter in a large bowl.
Gradually add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at
a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
At low speed, add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well after each addition.
Sprinkle with crumbs and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until cake springs back when touched in center.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In casserole dish, arrange broccoli, top with chicken. Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Mix together and press into a pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve juice and cook spaghetti. Put spaghetti in a large bowl and add soup, chopped chestnuts, Ro-Tel tomatoes, cheese, onion and bell peppers (that have been sauteed).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish or 2 smaller ones.
Put 1/2 cup cheese on top and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Slightly brown meat; add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Let simmer about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Mix well and let simmer for 25 minutes with lid on, then sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Let stand until cheese is melted.
Cook on top of stove or in 350° oven.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add buttermilk, egg and onion, mix well. Carefully drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil. Cook a few at a time, turning once. Fry until golden brown, drain. Yield 2-1/2 dozen.

title: swedish walnut cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Spread frosting on cake while warm, then refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salt water until just fork tender; drain.
In saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons margarine; add carrots and onions.
Saute until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/2 cups seasoned croutons, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini. Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining margarine and toss rest of the croutons.
Sprinkle these over top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes after mixture comes to a boil. Stir constantly while cooking.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla flavoring and mix well.
Add oatmeal and nuts and blend thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to dry before removing.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Mix milk, sugar, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in a large saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 12 minutes, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Beat until smooth.
Great on Chocolate Cake.

title: busy day fish
directions: Combine sour cream and soup mix in bowl.
Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan, parsley and paprika in shallow dish.
Dip fish in sour cream mix and then coat lightly with bread crumbs, etc.
Arrange fish in single layer in baking dish.
Pour oil over top.
Bake until fish is lightly browned about 8 minutes at 500°.
Turn and continue baking 5 more minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: no crust egg pies
directions: Mix all ingredients real good and pour in pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix pudding mix, jello powder and water/orange juice in pan. Bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Add fruits and frozen topping and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add the rest of ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on the box.
Drain well. Mix with rest of ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: fall apple nut slaw(diabetic)
directions: In a large bowl, combine coleslaw mix, red cabbage, apples and walnuts.

In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and sugar substitute. Add mayonnaise mixture to cabbage mixture. Mix well to combine. Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Gently stir again just before serving. Serves 8.

title: strawberry pie(no sugar included)
directions: Pour strawberries into baked pie crust.
Mix pudding with water and bring to a boil.
Add gelatin and stir well.
Pour over strawberries and chill well.

title: pudding mix cake
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: The first water and sugar, bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: b.b.q. meat loaves & cheddar potatoes
directions: Preheat boiler. Cover broiling rack with foil for easier cleaning. In medium bowl combine beef, egg, crumbs, salt and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce just until blended. On foil lined rack shape meat mixture into 4-inch long oval loaves. Broil meat loaves about 4 inches from heat for 12 minutes; turning over once; spoon remaining sauce on top. Heat potatoes and milk over medium heat until hot. Remove from heat and add cheddar cheese.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, green pepper and onions very thin.
Combine with vinegar, sugar and salt, approximately 1/2 gallon.
Put in refrigerator.

title: spinach with cream cheese casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt cream cheese in your casserole dish.
Drain spinach and mix with cream cheese.
Add onion soup mix and mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown and drain the ground round steak.
Meanwhile, pour the vegetable oil into a large saucepan and add the carrots, onions and celery.
Saute 5 minutes or cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flour or cornstarch.
Add and stir in the beef, broth, canned tomatoes, water, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt.
Add drained beef to soup; bring to a boil and simmer for 25 minutes. Stir in frozen peas and parsley and simmer 5 minutes more.
This is a doubled recipe; the original recipe calls for 1 pound of beef, so adjust to taste.

title: quick brown rice casserole
directions: Chop onion; saute in butter.
Put bouillon, consomme, rice and onion in casserole dish.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 450°.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, then mix all ingredients well into the eggs.
Put into pie pan; bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheesy bread
directions: Slice bread; do not cut through bottom of loaf.
Put a piece of cheese between the bread slices.
Sprinkle with garlic chips. Put on baking sheet and pour melted butter slowly over top.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
We love this with any soup!

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Fill a well-greased
casserole with alternate layers of seasoned
tomatoes, margarine
and	crumbs.
Have
last
layer margarine and crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Spray pan with non stick cooking spray. Measure flour in large bowl. Divide the shortening into small pieces and scatter on top of flour. Cut shortening into flour with a pastry cutter, two knifes or your finger tips until pieces are pea size. Stir in cheese and milk, stirring only enough to moisten flour and hold dough together. Drop by rounded Tbsp. onto prepared baking sheet, Bake 8-10 minutes or until tops are golden brown. Brush with garlic butter. (Combine butter and garlic until well blended.)

title: grandma craine's jello salad
directions: Add hot water to jello and stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise, milk, pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Top with cherries (just before serving).
It's best to prepare and refrigerate several hours before serving to let jello congeal.

title: irish soda bread(a st. patrick's day must!)
directions: Measure and sift together directly into a large bowl the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda. Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture is consistency of coarse corn meal. Add egg, raisins, buttermilk and seed.

Turn dough onto a well floured board. Using lightly floured fingers, knead dough lightly, then shape into a well-greased 8-inch round pan. With a sharp knife, lightly floured, make a lengthwise and crosswise cut through the dough. Bake in oven at 400° about 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: simply super cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball; chill until firm. Roll in pecans, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: patty's chinese chicken and vegetables
directions: Spread chicken pieces on waxed paper; brush with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides; drain oil from skillet.
Add sugar, pepper, celery, onions, broccoli and chicken broth.
Bring to boiling. Lower heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and soy sauce in a cup.
Stir into skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and clear.
Add tomato pieces and cook 1 minute longer.
Serve over rice.

title: sour cream-coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased 10-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: quick corned beef macaroni
directions: Place macaroni, soup, milk, water and chopped onion in a 2-quart ovenware casserole dish, covered.
Cook for 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Add corned beef and cheese.
Cover with onion rings.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture bubbles along edges.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: gourmet stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased casserole.
Bake uncovered in 250° oven for 6 hours.
Before serving, thicken if desired. Serve with mashed potatoes, rice or noodles.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until very thick.
Add sifted dry ingredients; beat smooth.
Add dates, vanilla and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in 1 x 4-inch bars while warm.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 2 dozen bars.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large Tupperware tub, combine all of the canned fruits and their juices.
Add jar of cherries and juice.
Add any amount of grapes.
Add sliced bananas and chunks of apples.
Mix well. Serve chilled.

title: macaroni-tomato casserole
directions: Cook
and
drain
macaroni;
cool
with
running water. Combine with cheese and set aside.	Soften onion, green pepper and celery in oil.
Add tomatoes and salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Combine
hot
and cold mixtures.
Place in a 2-quart casserole;	top
with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Buttered Bread Crumbs:
Melt butter in a small
skillet; add bread crumbs;
stir and cook until well coated and
slightly toasted.
If you would like, you can add up to
2 cups cubed left over roast beef, pork or chicken with the hot mixture.

title: ham and macaroni scallop
directions: Break macaroni into short lengths and cook in boiling salted water 9 minutes.
Make sauce by blending margarine and flour smoothly.
Add milk and stir until mixture boils; season with pepper.
Arrange in buttered casserole, alternating layers of macaroni, cheese, ham and sauce.
Top with buttered crumbs (additional grated cheese may be added).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cape cod october pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry rolled to 1/8-inch thickness.
Toss together the cranberries, apples, raisins and walnuts with the sugar, flour, cinnamon, cranberry juice and vanilla.
Spoon lightly into unbaked pie shell and dot with butter.
Cut strips from remaining pie crust and make a lattice over the top of pie.

title: loaf bread(from master bread mix)
directions: Beat egg until foamy; add oil and milk and beat well.
Stir in Bread Mix until thoroughly combined and let stand 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Spoon and spread batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center of loaf comes out clean.
