Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan, cool completely on rack.

title: macaroni seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package and rinse in cold water and drain.
Place in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, combine mayo, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except for green onions and tomatoes.
Toss gently.
Chill for 2 or 3 hours.
Add tomatoes and onions for garnish and serve.

title: canned green beans
directions: Let boil water, sugar and vinegar.
Add beans and boil again. Boil about 45 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars.
Add the 1 teaspoon salt to each jar, then pour boiling liquid solution over the beans.
Put on the hot top and ring and seal tightly.

title: golden meat loaf
directions: Blend the first 7 ingredients well.
Place in loaf pan.
Top with the brown sugar and mustard.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: number "1" peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly until it forms a stiff dough. Pinch off small balls and place them on an ungreased cookie sheet. Mash them flat with a fork.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 12 minutes (remove before they start to shrink).
Allow to cool briefly, then loosen with spatula.
Let cookies cool completely before putting away.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well and allow to stand for about 1 minute.
Roll into little balls and serve.

title: brioche (french rolls)
directions: In a saucepan, scald milk.
Stir in butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In a bowl, combine milk, yeast, salt, sugar and 1 cup flour.
Add eggs; mix well. Mix in remaining 1 cup flour.
Chill in refrigerator overnight. Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth.
Divide into 2 portions.
Shape each portion into 9 balls.
Place 16 balls in greased, fluted brioche cups.
Shape the remaining 3 balls of dough into 16 small balls.
Place 1 small ball in a shallow cut made on top of each roll.
Let rise, covered, in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Yields 16 rolls.

title: sicilian rigatoni and sausage
directions: In medium skillet, cook sausage, green pepper and onion until sausage is cooked through and vegetables are tender; drain.
Stir in Pasta Sauce, sugar and fennel.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, 1 cup sugar, cocoa and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of filling into egg yolks, stir and then mix it back into filling.
Cook 1 minute.
Add margarine and vanilla; cool slightly.
Cover with meringue made of egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: super smoking sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Paint on meat surfaces before, once during and at end of smoking.
Keeps indefinitely refrigerated.
Enough sauce for 16 chickens or two turkeys.
Also good for beef, ham or lamb.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add lard.
Mix well.
Mixture will look coarse.
Mix egg, water and vinegar together.
Add to flour mixture.
Shape into a ball of dough.
Makes 2 (2 crust) pies.

title: melts in your mouth dessert
directions: *Can use grated chocolate.

title: coconut peaks
directions: Slowly melt butter until golden brown.
Stir in powdered sugar, coconut and cream.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Refrigerate until easy to handle, then shape into peaks. Over hot, not boiling, water melt chocolate pieces and shortening. Stir until smooth.
Dip bottoms of the peaks into chocolate, then harden on wax paper.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Melt 5 cups marshmallows, corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Mix quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Stir in 1 cup marshmallows.

title: creamy skillet potatoes(ultra low-fat)
directions: Precook potatoes in microwave until slightly tender.
Spray a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Brown onions and potatoes.
When potatoes are golden brown, add all remaining ingredients and simmer until sauce thickens.
Serve warm.
Great side dish with almost any meal.
Entire recipe makes 6 servings. Less than 1 gram of fat per serving.
Calories per serving: 114.

title: sauteed brussels sprouts with raisins
directions: Heat oil in large skillet in medium heat.
Add Brussels sprouts and carrots; saute until sprouts start to turn golden brown (about 3 minutes).
Add raisins and chicken broth.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until sprouts are tender when pierced with a paring knife (about 12 minutes).
If the skillet becomes too dry before sprouts are tender, add up to 3 tablespoons of water and continue cooking.
Remove from heat and season with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Add corn to margarine.
Stir in sour cream.
Add eggs.
Stir in cornbread mix.
Pour into oblong casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° or until golden brown or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: ole san antonio pralines
directions: Mix sugar, milk, baking soda and salt. Cook very slowly to soft ball, 234°, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add oleo, vanilla and pecans. Beat until creamy and drop on waxed paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion until brown.
Add pork and beans, 1/2 pound brown sugar and ketchup.
Simmer on top of stove until done (cook in iron skillet on top of stove).

title: dexter's sour cream stew
directions: Saute onions in olive oil until light brown, over high heat. Reduce heat to medium-high.
Add meat and stir occasionally until browned.
Drain fat.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, tomato sauce and vegetables. Add 1 soup can of water.
Stir and cover.
Simmer at medium-high for 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: frosted white cake with almond filling
directions: Combine shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add baking powder to flour and sift 3 times.
Add small amounts of flour to creamed mixture, alternately with combined milk and water, mixing after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold carefully into mixture until well blended.
Pour batter into two 9-inch layer pans greased with pan coat.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Spread Toasted Almond Filling between layers and Seven Minute Frosting on top and sides of cake.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix oil, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, flour, egg and milk.

title: betty's pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Place in an 8-inch square casserole dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese. Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger cornbread pie
directions: Brown meat in skillet and add onions.
Add chili powder, salt, Worcestershire and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes and add beans. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix Jiffy cornbread muffin mix according to directions on the box and add to the top of meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake 35 minutes in a 350° to 375° oven.
Add cheese last and bake 10 minutes longer.
Use an 8 x 10-inch pan (approximate).

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown ground beef seasoning with Italian seasoning and garlic salt.
Drain.
Stir in sharp Cheddar cheese.
Spread on round breads.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 6 to 8 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Serve.
May make ahead and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: veal croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Cool on a buttered plate. Shape, dip in crumbs, egg and crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat and drain.

title: berry berry berry pie
directions: Mix berries in large bowl; drain.
Pour into pastry shell. Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pastry shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over pie before serving.
Garnish with additional berries if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: honey spice bars
directions: Mix and pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice with:

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs, 5 whites and 5 yolks.
First, beat egg whites in a small bowl.
Set aside.
In a LARGE bowl, cream sugar, margarine, and Crisco.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut. Fold in the egg whites just until they are incorporated into the batter.
Pour into 3 well greased cake pans.
Use 2 ovens as the third layer doesn't bake evenly if baked with the other two.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes until done.
Cool before icing.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine sugar, 1 stick melted butter or margarine and cracker crumbs.
Mix well and line a 9 x 12-inch dish or pan with crumbs.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter 2-quart casserole.
Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup with 1 cup water.
Place 1 cup quick rice in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over rice.
Sprinkle 1/2 package dry onion soup mix over this.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place on top of soup and rice mixture.
Sprinkle with other 1/2 package onion soup mix.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cherry pretzel torte
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on crust.
Top with pie filling.
Top with remaining pretzel mixture.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Combine gravy, mushrooms, chicken, milk, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Add spaghetti and mix well.
Pour into large baking dish.
Sprinkle top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until bubbly and lightly brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries in food processor.
Add sugar; mix well. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Add all ingredients except apples.
Add apples a few hours before serving.

title: roasted soy beans
directions: Soak beans in water and baking soda for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain; mix in salt.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Roast in microwave about 10 minutes.
Stir at intervals.
Cook a little longer to make crisper.
It's good to make a double batch!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat eggs, then add to batter.
Add salt and baking powder.
Add 1/3 cup of the milk.
Sift 1/3 cup of the sifted flour to batter.
Repeat this step two more times, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into prepared baking pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: 20-minute cake
directions: Slice cake in half.
Mix pudding, pineapple and Cool Whip together.
Place half of the mixture between cake "halves."
Put the other half of the mixture on top of cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and walnuts.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Then mix together cream cheese, 1/2 of large Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Spread over crust.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread marshmallows on top. Bake until the marshmallows begin to turn brown.
Bake at 300°. Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour. Add milk, butter and vanilla. Pour in a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sausage bites
directions: Mix ingredients together and spoon on individual chips or bread slices and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until melted.

title: stewed peaches
directions: Pare and quarter peaches and remove stones.
Add a small amount of cold water (about 1/2 cup).
Cover and heat slowly. Simmer until peaches are soft, 5 to 15 minutes.
Stir sugar into hot peaches.
Chill and serve.
Makes 5 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Crumble Town House crackers over the top and drizzle a little soft butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast the oats
directions: Dissolve Vegex in 4 tablespoons of hot water.
Combine all ingredients, except mushroom soup and water.
Blend well and fry in patties.
Place in casserole dish and cover with mushroom soup diluted with water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: buttercream wedding cake frosting
directions: Beat all together with mixer for 10 minutes on high speed. Left overs will keep 3 weeks in container at room temperature.

title: spinach pies(spanakopita)
directions: Wash spinach and discard stems.
Dry as thoroughly as possible on absorbent paper and cut in small pieces.
Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add spinach and saute a few minutes longer.
Set aside to cool.
Add eggs, cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Cut fillo leaf to desired width and butter (cut leaf in half).
Center a spoonful of filling at the bottom of leaf, about 1 inch from edge.
Fold 1 inch of the leaf over mixture; fold side edge in 1 inch and fold an angle, starting from lower right corner.
Keep folding in the shape of a triangle. Cut off any excess.
Place on buttered pan and butter the triangle.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ice cream sandwich cake
directions: Layer ice cream sandwiches, cool whip, ice cream sandwiches, cool whip - crush candy bars and sprinkle on top.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Heat butter and oil in oblong baking dish in a 400° oven. Place chicken in dish, turning to coat with butter.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Mix soup, mushrooms (with liquid), water, Worcestershire sauce and thyme. Rinse and drain frozen vegetables.
Mix vegetables with chicken. Spoon soup mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Cook, uncovered, until done, about 30 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Place berries in long, flat Pyrex casserole dish and sprinkle the sugar on top. Seal with foil and cook in 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes (berries should pop open when done). Stir to dissolve sugar. Stir in marmalade, ginger and nuts while berries are hot. Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk, dry ingredients and extracts.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces; set aside.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Alternate layers, beginning with angel cake, cheese mixture and end with cherries on top.
Decorate with cream, if you like.

title: cabbage soup (low carb)
directions: Add chicken broth to large pot.
Add cabbage and sliced radishes to broth.

title: hidden treasure cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Fill cupcake holders 2/3 full.
(I put cupcake liners in the muffin pan.)
Beat cream cheese with sugar until creamy.
Beat in salt and egg.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful into center of each cupcake.
Bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cut and mix raisins, prunes, figs, candied citron, orange peel and cherries.
Add jelly, juice and spices.
Let stand overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake in loaf pans at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Bring
milk, vanilla, and sugar to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cut biscuits into small squares and add to mix until thickens.
Cook 2-3 minutes and pour into baking dish.

title: light alfredo sauce
directions: Bring the evaporated milk to a simmer over moderate heat. Stir in cheese and when it is thick, serve immediately over cooked pasta.
Fettuccine is preferred with Alfredo.
Season to taste.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix well and serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp with a southern accent
directions: Prepare rice as usual.
Place shrimp in boiling water; cook for 5 minutes.
Use large skillet and melt butter at low heat. Combine pepper and onion in skillet with butter.
Cook on low heat until tender.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Pour into skillet. Add garlic salt and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp to sauce. Cook for a further 10 minutes.
Place rice on large platter, making a well in the center.
Place shrimp Creole in center. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Mix well and bake for 10 minutes at 350°; stir once.
Freezes well.

title: supermoist chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixer bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).

title: jerky
directions: Mix all marinade ingredients in bowl. Pour over meat slices; thoroughly wet all sides of meat and layer in the marinating dish. Cover tightly the marinade in refrigerator overnight. If possible, rotate meat layers every few hours. Drain marinated meat and spread in single layer in dehydrator.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, oregano, pepper and onion salt in a saucepan.
Saute onions and garlic in oil for 10 minutes.
Fry ground beef until brown and add onions to tomato mixture; simmer 5 minutes.

title: marge's fruit dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Great with all types of fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg to dry ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Put sliced apples in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish; add 1/2 cup sugar (or to taste) and cinnamon (to taste).
Top with crumbly mixture.
Melt 1 stick of margarine; pour over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown.
(Recipe may be doubled for a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.)

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pot roast(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in ovenproof casserole.
Sear beef 6 to 8 minutes over medium-high heat on all sides.
Season well.

title: broccoflower au gratin
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as package directs.
Drain.
Place in greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Blend soup with milk and pour over vegetables.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: john wayne cheese casserole
directions: Remove seeds from chiles. Cut into large pieces. Combine cheese and chilies. Turn into a shallow greased 2-quart casserole dish. In large bowl, beat egg whites just until stiff peaks form. In small bowl, combine egg yolks, milk, flour, salt and pepper. Mix until well blended. Using a rubber spatula, gently fold beaten egg whites into yolk mixture. Pour over cheese casserole and using 2 forks, ooze it through the cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven. Overlap tomato slices at edge of casserole. Bake 30 minutes longer or until knife blade comes out clean. Can
also add cubes of ham. Serves 8.

title: dill and onion dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with crackers or raw veggies.

title: sugar cure for meat
directions: Rub in meat well (fresh cured pork) and wrap.
Hang up to season 4 to 6 weeks.
Cure meat during cool weather, not freezing nor during hot summer (35° to 47°).

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the tomato sauce and the taco seasoning mix.
Stir to mix well.
Line bottom of an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with 2 cups of the corn chips; crush the remaining chips and set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over corn chips.
Combine the remaining tomato sauce and the refried beans.
Spread over cooked ground beef mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes or until mixture is heated through.
Sprinkle the Cheddar cheese and crushed corn chips on top and bake for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apricot muffins(low-fat)
directions: Chop apricots; cover with 1/4 cup of water and let stand. Spray nonstick oil in muffin tin.
Stir baking soda and yogurt together.
Combine sugar, whole wheat flour, flour and baking powder.
Stir in yogurt, oil, eggs and almond extract until combined.
Fold in apricots.
Spoon into tins.
Bake 15 minutes until golden brown in a 375° oven.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook for about 1 hour before mixing. Add remaining ingredients to beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in tiny balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water in a bowl; stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add strawberries; chill 30 minutes or until partially set.
Add pineapple and pecans; stir well.
Spread half of gelatin mixture evenly into an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray; chill slightly.
Stir sour cream into remaining gelatin mixture; spread evenly into pan.
Chill 20 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 9 servings.

title: sherbet
directions: To make your own sherbet at half the cost of ready made, simply place 2 cups milk, 1 cup sugar and 1 package of unsweetened Kool-Aid (any flavor) in blender.
Blend until well mixed.
Pour into an ice cube tray or loaf pan and freeze.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except sliced pineapple.
Bake at 350° until brown or onions are tender.
Place pineapple rings on top of beans when done.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Let cream cheese and butter soften at room temperature; blend. Stir in flour.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape in 2 dozen 1-inch balls; place in tiny ungreased muffin cups.
Press against bottom and sides.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Fritos and chill for few hours or overnight. Toss in Fritos just before serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix salt and chopped vegetables; let set overnight.
Drain well.
Rinse with water.
Bring rest of ingredients to a boil; simmer 3 minutes, then add vegetables.
Bring to a boil; simmer 3 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use the amount of each according to how many you are serving. This makes a delicious salad if you don't like Waldorf Salad with mayonnaise.

title: frijitas
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate 2 hours, if possible.
Put on cookie sheet and broil until browned.
Turn with spatula often. Cooks in approximately 15 minutes, if that.

title: maple baked acorn squash
directions: Cut the squash into halves.
Remove seeds and fibers.
Place squash, cut sides up, in ungreased baking pan. Spoon the syrup and cream into each half.
Cook, uncovered, in
a 350° oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit cheesecakes
directions: Cream the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Beat in eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spoon into muffin tin about 2/3 full. Bake 40 minutes at 300°. Remove and cool. Then combine sour cream, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Top each cake with mixture. Return to oven for 5 minutes. Cool. Top with fruit or pie filling. Makes about 18 mini cheesecakes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Let cool slightly.
Add peaches and undrained pineapple.
Let jell.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Spread over jello mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and mayonnaise. Put broccoli in 2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Melt butter and put in dressing; add to top of broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add peanut butter.
Sift all dry ingredients and add gradually to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Roll to size of a walnut and flatten with a wet fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil in heavy frypan; remove.
Add onion, soup and milk to fat in pan; blend.
Set aside.
Starting with potatoes, put alternate layers of potatoes and cabbage into casserole; sprinkle each layer with flour.
Pour soup sauce over each layer. Place pork chops on top.
Cover casserole or use foil to cover pan. Bake 1 1/4 hours in oven at 350°.

title: stir-fry beef with broccoli
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; combine with soy sauce, garlic and 2 tablespoons of broth.
Marinate while preparing the vegetables.
Cut and wash broccoli flowerets. I don't use the large stalk part of the broccoli but if you do use them, you need to peel them and cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Wash, peel and cut carrots into strips or slice thinly crosswise.
Cut onion.

title: banana-split cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake according to package instructions.
Mix in banana slices.
Place in shell.
Cover with crushed pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with Hershey's syrup and place cherries on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: freezer pudding pops
directions: Mix together all ingredients (do not beat).
Pour into molds and freeze just until firm.
Put in popsicle sticks.
Return to freezer.
Makes 10 pops.

title: squash shells
directions: Boil squash half done; cut in halves.
Remove center with spoon into mixing bowl.
Cut up through squash neck.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill shells.
Bake at 350° until browned.
May be frozen on wax paper covered cookie sheet, then placed in freezer bags until needed.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt on pickles, let stand 2 hours, then drain off. mix vinegar and sugar, boil 5 minutes,
let cool, when cool pour over pickles. Put in boxes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with no-stick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar and all dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, whip egg whites lightly.
Stir in mashed bananas, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture; stir until well blended.

title: brown bag a.m. delight muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add oil, milk and vanilla. Mix well and stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.
Yield: 1 1/2 doz.

title: chocolate trifle pudding
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir together milk and whipping cream. Cook over medium heat until warm.
In small bowl, stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Gradually add milk to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, except sweetened whipped cream.
Continue cooking.
Stir constantly until it begins to thicken.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Cover then refrigerate 2 hours. Add sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle with cocoa.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: In a bowl, melt almond bark in microwave.
In another bowl, melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Combine two mixtures and add peanuts.
Spoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all liquids. Heat last 5 ingredients. Cool. Pour over vegetables and chill overnight.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: In blender, grind cranberries and apples together.
Place in small bowl with sugar; let stand 30 minutes.
In large bowl, dissolve jello in water.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until partly molded.
Fold in pineapple, cranberry mix, grapes and walnuts.
Pour in a 6-cup mold or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: western hash
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Top with grated cheese if desired.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach. Cut butter or margarine into pieces. Beat eggs until frothy. Cut cheese into cubes. Thoroughly combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Pour into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Lay ham slices out.
Spread cream cheese on slices.
Lay onion on one edge and start rolling up.
Chill rolls about 20 minutes, then slice into pinwheels.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook one pkg. spaghetti, broken into quarters. Mix ingredients and pour over spaghetti and toss. Chill and serve.

title: shiny top cobbler
directions: Spread berries in 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk, oleo, 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking powder.
Mix well and pour over berries.
In small bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spread over cake mixture. Cover with boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable garden relish
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Chop onions and peppers.
Chop tomatoes fine.
Add 1/2 cup salt and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat until hot.
Add drained vegetables.
Bring to boiling point and seal.
Very tasty.
I also use this in potato salad and tuna salad.

title: pan-fry smelts
directions: Dip each smelt in flour.
Dip in egg.
Dip in breadcrumbs.
Let dry on a rack for a few minutes.
Fry a few at a time in oil.
Fry for 2 minutes.
Turn and fry for 2 minutes more.

title: finger jello
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in large jelly roll pan. Put in refrigerator 2 hours.
Cut in squares.
Will not stick to fingers.

title: chocolate zucchini bread(4th place at montgomery co. fair, maryland)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until light and thick.
Add applesauce and zucchini.
Stir.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into zucchini mixture until just blended.
Fold in nuts and chocolate if desired.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until a cake tester comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pans and cool completely on rack.

title: cucumber molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix this with the lemon Jell-O and 1 cup hot water; let cool.
Add salt and vinegar; stir.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise, cucumber, onion and pimientos.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir whipped topping into marshmallow cream. Stir in mint extract and food coloring.
Fold in chopped mint wafers.
Spoon onto Oreo pie crust.
Freeze at least 4 hours.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Cowboy Cake, so called because it contains or requires no ingredients that cannot be carried or preserved in chuck wagon.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix jello and water. Beat eggs. Add oil and berries. Blend in box of cake mix and jello. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Stir over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Pour into 2 sets Tupperware Ice Tups and freeze or pour into popsicle trays.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables halfway done.
Heat soup (undiluted). Arrange vegetables in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over all and add cheese.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight, and then drain water before cooking.
Put ham bone in large pot, cover and cook for 1/2 hour.
Add whole peas, onion, bay leaf, parsley, and cook slow for about 2 hours. Remove ham bone from pan and set aside to cool, take any small pieces apart to add to soup later.
Add split peas, carrots, celery and cook for 1 more hour.
Make sure to keep adding hot water to cover peas at all times.
Check if peas are cooked and soup has thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste...bonne appetit.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Place flour, oregano, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Twist top and shake to mix.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Toss meat in bag with flour to coat.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Cook sausage, drain and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients plus 1 tablespoon sausage grease.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put sausage in pan, top with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over sausage mixture.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: her lady ship cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk.
Stir in baking powder; beat thoroughly. Add vanilla.
Blend egg mixture into margarine and sugar mixture, then mix well.
Add coconut and stir in flour, slowly.
Add graham cracker crumbs, a little at a time, making sure you mix well. Stir in cup of nuts.
Cut wax paper to fit in bottom of tube pan. Do not grease pan.
Pour batter into pan and cut gently with a knife to remove any air bubbles.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until cake leaves sides of pan.
Eat and enjoy.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine.
Spread in a pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix chicken with all other ingredients except the corn flakes.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish; top with crushed corn flakes and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dump pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix pie filling, pineapple and sugar together.
Spread in dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over all.
Slice oleo over top.
Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake 1 hour.

title: homemade brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter. Add cocoa.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and cocoa mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: buttermilk fried chicken(makes 6 servings.)
directions: Combine flour and Mrs. Dash.
Cut each breast half into 3 pieces.
Coat evenly with flour mixture.
Dip into buttermilk and coat with remaining flour mixture.
Place in a baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Drizzle with margarine. Cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Each serving contains 265 calories.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins with water until the water is gone.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Alternate adding flour, raisins and vanilla.
Make balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (not too dark).
Makes 8 dozen.

title: baked carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute chopped onion in butter about 3 minutes.
Mix with carrots.
Pour mixture in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, sugar, water and cover.
Bake until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Bake in 9
x 13-inch pan for 55 minutes at 350°.
Place in pan in
exact order listed: cherry pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, butter, coconut and nuts.

title: shrimp entree soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in a Dutch oven. Drain and crumble bacon. Saute onion and garlic over moderately low heat in 2 tablespoons bacon fat until onion is transparent. Add tomatoes and liquid. Add green pepper, red pepper sauce, black pepper, bay leaf, carrots, celery, potatoes and salt.

Bring to boiling point, reduce heat and simmer, covered, until potatoes are done. Add shrimp (canned shrimp should be drained and rinsed in cold water). Continue to cook until shrimp are heated through. Cook until just done.
Remove bay leaf. Garnish each serving with crumbled bacon (optional). Serve with corn bread.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper; brown in medium size skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add one cup apple juice and water; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add raisins; place lemon slice on each pork chop.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes longer or until pork chops are tender.
Remove pork chops from skillet.
Mix remaining one half cup of apple juice and dry gravy mix, stirring until smooth; add to pan juices.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Serve gravy over pork chops.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread, then add cherry pie filling.
Dump dry cake mix over evenly.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Melt margarine or butter and spread over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except water; form into balls.
Brown slightly in small amount of butter.
Add water; cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: the lin-nott
directions: Mix.
Take your shoes off cos you won't be going anywhere after this.

title: dave's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend with butter and sugar mixture, then add flour, almond extract and candied fruit.
Butter and flour a loaf pan or a Bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool for 15 minutes and then put on serving dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions. In medium bowl, combine soup, chicken, cheese (both kinds), green onions, peas and corn; mix well. In 2-quart baking dish, layer in sauce, rice, sauce, rice, then remaining sauce. Sprinkle the 1/2 cup Romano cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour and pecans.
Melt margarine and pour into the flour mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Press mixture in the bottom of a large Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip to form the second layer and place in dish.
Mix instant pudding and 3 cups milk and place in dish for the third layer.
Spread large container of Cool Whip over third layer and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Cream sugar and shortening thoroughly and add egg.
Sift together dry ingredients and add all together with milk.

title: chicken in white wine and yogurt sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in shallow 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Place chicken in pan.
Bake, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.

title: mom's cheese cake
directions: Make a crust from graham crackers in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix all together, except pie filling.
Pour into crust and put cherry pie filling on top.

title: fruitcake
directions: Grease three 8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Preheat oven to 275°.

title: olive hors d'oeuvers
directions: Mix first three ingredients with fingers.
Wrap each olive in cheese dough - cover completely until sealed.
Bake 15 - 20 minutes at 350°.
These can be made ahead and frozen by placing on pan separately to freeze and then putting into bag in freezer. Place on cooking sheet frozen and bake.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add to eggs and stir.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Beat in bananas.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well; cover.
Chill at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Add lemon juice to milk.
Add pineapple to nuts; stir real good.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into pie shells.
Refrigerate for a short time.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine in bowl; mix well. Cream sugar and cream cheese in small mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in mixture of topping mix and milk.
Spread half the cracker crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cream cheese mixture, pie filling and remaining cracker crumb mixture in prepared dish.
Chill, covered, until serving time.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: golden valley cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
While cake is baking, boil the pineapple and sugar.
Puncture cake with fork after baking, pour over pineapple mixture.	Let cake cool. Prepare pudding mix according to directions.
Spread on cool cake. Let cake completely cool, then spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
The longer this cake sets, the better it gets.
Let set at least 2 or 3 days.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Place beans in large kettle; cover with water.
Soak beans overnight.
Drain beans and cover with fresh water.
Cook over medium heat 2 hours or until tender. Drain thoroughly.
Combine beans, puree, water, bacon and chili powder.
Saute onion in butter, margarine or bacon fat for 5 minutes.
Add to beans.
Simmer beans 30 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch angel food cake pan.
Cream the butter.
Add the cream cheese; beat until fluffy. Add sugar; beat 3 minutes.
Add lemon juice, vanilla and lemon peel.
Add eggs, 2 at a time; beat until combined.
Add flour and salt; beat until smooth and creamy.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple crumble
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut butter into dry cake mix to form pea size crumbs.
Sprinkle over apple mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven.
Bake approximately 40 minutes. Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: sour cream and raisin bars
directions: Cook together raisins and water; drain and cool.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, oatmeal, flour, margarine, soda and salt.
Put 1/2 the batter into a 9 x 13 pan.
Press down.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Mix eggs, sour cream, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix well and cook until thick, stirring.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Pour over baked crust and sprinkle with remainder of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in chicken broth until tender.
Cook; chop, discarding bones and broth.
Bring to boil the chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Add Veg-All, dried onion flakes and black pepper and simmer until onions have time to flavor the mix.
Melt butter.
Stir in milk and flour into the butter to form a batter. Pour the chicken mixture into a 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Spoon the batter over the top.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: patio beans
directions: Mix well. Put in baking dish. Bake at 400° until as dry as you like it.

title: cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Beat cream cheese and salad dressing together.
Add olive juice and refrigerate until thickens.
Stir in olives and nuts. Serve on dark rye bread.

title: coconut butter pecan cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Beat well. Fold in frosting mix. Add pecans. Heat oven to 350°. Pour in greased tube pan. Cook 1 hour. Cool and turn out on cake plate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, buttermilk and melted butter.
Add flour, mashed bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Add cracker crumbs.
Turn into buttered casserole dish.
Top with crackers. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, cook and stir confectioners coating and chips until melted and smooth. Cool for 10 minutes; stir in peanuts. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto waxed paper-lined baking sheets. Refrigerate until firm, about 45 minutes. Yield: 10 dozen.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together.
Add to the first mixture, except zucchini.
Add zucchini last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° until done.
Test with toothpick; done if toothpick comes out clean.

title: lili's favorite buttercream frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, beat together sugar, eggs, yolks, chocolate, coffee powder and vanilla; cook, stirring over simmering water, 10 to 15 minutes, or until thickened.
Cool completely.
With electric mixer, beat butter until fluffy; gradually beat into it the chocolate mixture.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lake superior whitefish cakes
directions: Using chopping board, chop whitefish into flakes, putting in bowl as you go.
Chop onion; add to bowl.
Beat egg.
Stir into fish mixture.
Stir in flour and spices.
Gradually add milk, stirring until mixture is light and fluffy.
Heat oil at 375°
or when a drop of water sizzles.
Dip spoon in cold water, then in fish mixture to scoop out cakes.
Roll in bread to cover.
Fry in hot oil turning once, about 4 minutes
on each side, depending on how large they are.
Drain on paper towel before serving.
Great with a cheese sauce, creamed peas, tartar sauce or a brown butter sauce.
Also great as an appetizer served hot or cold (making smaller balls).

title: lois' spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion, celery, beef and pork (if pork is used, eliminate salt).
Add to tomato mixture which includes all of the remaining ingredients.
Add 3 bay leaves.
Remove later.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts sauce.
Freeze some for later.

title: coconut impossible pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour, eggs and milk until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice when cool.
Garnish with nuts.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pans.
Beat butter at medium mixer speed until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and rum extract.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling about 3/4 full.
Sprinkle batter with sugar and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place all items in a large plastic bag. Shake until evenly coated.
Bake in a shallow roasting pan for 40 minutes or until the potatoes are tender and golden brown. Stir occasionally. Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: "people puppy chow"
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in large saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add cereal; stir gently until coated.
Place confectioners sugar in large paper bag or plastic bag.
Transfer cereal to bag and shake until cereal is coated. Spread in thin layer on several cookie sheets.
Let stand until dry.
Store in covered container.

title: lentil vegetable soup
directions: Rinse lentils; drain and place in large saucepan.
Add the water, onion, celery, carrot, garlic powder, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add sliced frankfurters.
Heat through, about 5 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spray 9x13 inch baking dish.
In medium saucepan, melt cheese, add rotel.
Layer: tortilla chips, chicken, onion, soup mixture, top with cheese mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Combine the oil and sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Gradually add the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add carrots and mix well. Pour batter into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool.
Ice with Nut Icing.

title: nutty cheese log
directions: In skillet, melt butter and add pecans.
Saute over low heat until lightly browned.
Cool and chop fine.
Stir in salt and parsley.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add milk, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce to cheeses.
Chill until firm for one hour.
Roll cheese into log using wax paper.
Roll in nut mixture.
Wrap airtight and chill overnight.
Makes a 7-inch log; serves 4. Serve with fruit, crackers or crudities.
A sparkling wine of your choice would be a festive touch.

title: "dirt" cakes
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. In a separate bowl, combine pudding mix, Cool Whip and milk; mix until smooth.
Add creamed ingredients and beat well.
Layer crushed Oreos and pudding mixture in clean 8-inch plastic flowerpot (or several small individual pots); start and end with Oreos.
Refrigerate until set.
Decorate with artificial flowers or gummi worms if desired.
For even more fun, serve with a gardening tool!

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and bananas; mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in persimmon pulp.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add nuts, raisins and spices to flour.
Beat egg and add to pulp.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Beat in Cool Whip.
Cut up bananas and add the pudding mixture with a spoon; stir well.
Put a layer of cookies in bowl; pour a layer of mixture over the cookies. Keep layering cookies and mixture.
On top, lay cookies flat.

title: oil pie shell
directions: Stir flour and salt together.
Pour water and oil into flour mixture and blend lightly with a fork.
Form into a ball.
Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Refrigerate for a few minutes. Peel off top piece of wax paper.
Fit dough paper side up into 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Remove paper.
Cut off excess pastry.
Flute edges.
Bake in a 450° oven for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
May also fill with a filling and then bake.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix everything together, except brown sugar. Pour this mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar over batter and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lo-cal hot apple chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, apple, celery and onion in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing until well blended.

title: cinnamon carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 3-inch strips.
Place in a large skillet with 1/2 cup water, butter and salt.
Cover and until tender-crisp. Stir in cinnamon, honey and lemon juice.
Add walnuts and simmer for several minutes, stirring constantly.

title: banana cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 9 x 13 pan with shortening and flour.

title: elegant baloney and cracker sandwich(emergency sandwich for the self-sufficient male)
directions: Creating A Baloney Cracker Sandwich:
Use the knife's sharpest blade to peel and slice the onion into 3/8-inch slices.
Care needs to be taken to make sure people do not see you if the onion makes your eyes water, because they may think you are soft and emotional.
tags: knife blades full of regular salad style yellow mustard

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocados with onion and seasonings.
Add tomato and French dressing and mix until smooth.
Serve chilled on shredded lettuce.
Serves 6.
(I sometimes use this recipe for dip.)

title: miniature cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at time, mixing until smooth after each addition.
Drop teaspoonfuls of batter onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil butter, sugar and syrup over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over popped corn in a greased bowl.
Mix well.
Put in oven at 250° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: honey french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended.
Pour into bottle or jar and refrigerate.
Shake well before using on combination salad, plain lettuce or cabbage slaw.
This dressing is particularly good on spinach salad.

title: hot german potato salad(microwave)
directions: Wash and pierce potatoes with fork.
Place in microwave; cook on High 10 to 12 minutes, turning over and rearranging after 4 minutes or until tender.
Remove and cool slightly.
Peel potatoes and cut in 1/8-inch slices to make about 4 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix flour, melted butter, eggs, sugar, sour cream, baking powder, salt and flavoring; mix well.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cheese, soup (undiluted), sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Fold in hash browns.
Turn mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Toss
together
corn
flakes
and
1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle
onto
potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until potatoes are golden brown or until tender.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls.
Add teaspoon of pumpkin mix to each crescent roll.
Roll crescent roll over like a turnover.
Bake according to crescent roll directions.
Enjoy with Cool Whip or drizzled icing.

title: vanilla frozen yogurt
directions: Combine sugar, gelatin and salt in a medium saucepan; add milk and let stand one minute.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, five minutes or until gelatin and sugar dissolve; let cool.
Stir in yogurt and vanilla; chill.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a gallon freezer.
Serve immediately or let ripen 1 hour.
Yields 10 1/2 cups; contains 84 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: coconut crunch pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites, vanilla and salt until egg whites form stiff peaks.
Fold graham cracker mixture with egg white mixture.
Spread in well-greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in wedges.
Serve with ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cream cheese. Add sugar. Cream sugar, cheese and salt together until creaming. Beat until stiff with the Dream Whip. Put beater on low and blend together. Pour into graham cracker crust. Use a No. 2 can Great Value pie filling. You can use cherry. Mix Dream Whip as it tells on the box.

title: potato flake bread
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and salt, water, starter and flour. Put into a large greased bowl, cover lightly and leave all night at room temperature.
Punch down and knead a few times.
If using 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans, divide dough in half.
Knead each part 8 to 10 times.
Put into greased pans.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, 1 to 5 hours.
Bake at 325°
for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on the size of pans used.

title: darlene's mexican fudge
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Put 1/2 cheese in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix eggs and taco sauce together.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Put on remainder of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: strawberry and fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello and gelatin in boiling water.
After mix is dissolved, add crushed pineapple (with juice) and sliced strawberries (thawed) and well mashed bananas.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream over layer.
Spoon on remainder of strawberry mixture and refrigerate.

title: hamburger carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put meat in bottom of slightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put layer of onions and carrots, ending with layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and water; mix until smooth.
Pour evenly over vegetables and meat.
Bake 90 minutes.

title: spaghetti(very good)
directions: Mix ground beef and pork (I use sausage) and form balls.
Fry meat balls, garlic and onion in olive oil.
Brown meat well.
Add tomato juice, paste, salt, red pepper and oregano.
Simmer 2 hours, covered.
Then add cream of mushroom soup and Parmesan cheese.
Combine spaghetti (cooked).
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with green pepper rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
It is not necessary to bake.

title: rice krispies
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add all together before the last 3 ingredients. Blend all these together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: yummy cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sponge cake
directions: Put egg whites in small bowl and set aside.
Put egg yolks in a separate bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to mixture.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix all together; will be very thick.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package.
Drain well; set aside. Combine cream cheese & butter.
Beat on medium with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in spinach.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for
20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart casserole. Layer half of pie filling and half the dry cake mix.
Repeat layers.
Pour melted Crisco evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza pie
directions: Lightly brown garlic in a little butter or oleo.
Add tomatoes and cook until most of juice is gone.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Dice vegetables and place in pot.
Cover with juice from clams and cook until tender.
While vegetables are cooking, prepare sauce.
Combine melted butter and flour with salt and pepper. Cook for 1 minute and add sugar to half and half.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add to vegetables and add clams.
Heat for an additional 30 minutes on low.

title: hot crab meat
directions: Place crab meat in saucepan with melted butter, celery and onion.
Stir until heated.
Add flour and milk.
Stir to thick enough to spread.
Spread on small rye bread, toasted, or wheat crackers.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until done; skin and slice.
Mix sugar, water and vinegar.
Pour over beets and boil 15 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 to 3 minutes at a rapid boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: fried chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Wash and dry chicken; coat pieces in flour mixture.
In a skillet, melt shortening to 1/2-inch depth over medium-high heat.
Fry chicken (in batches if necessary) in hot shortening until golden brown on all sides. Return all chicken to pan; cover and cook over low heat until chicken is done, about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat beans thoroughly. Drain.
Mix with mushroom soup.
Place in casserole. Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until rings are brown, 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb supreme
directions: Pour over rhubarb and bake for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together salt, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Mix together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Spray with Pam or grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or make 3 layers.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: seaside salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill.

title: southern fried okra
directions: Wash okra.
Cut in 1 inch slices.
Combine egg and milk, beating well.
Combine flour and cornmeal, sprinkle okra with salt and pepper.
Dip okra in egg mixture and dredge in flour mixture. Heat oil to 375 degrees.
Place dredged okra in wire basket (just enough to cover bottom of basket).	Place basket in deep fat for 1-3 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: maine blueberry pudding
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 10 minutes.
Layer slices of buttered bread with blueberry mixture in loaf pan.
Chill in refrigerator several hours.
Slice and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Add half of melted butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Pour corn mixture into pan.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: turkey cabbage soup(easy, delicious, healthy!)
directions: In a large pot, brown the turkey with the onion, breaking meat into small bits. Drain off any fat.
Add the tomato juice, cabbage, carrots, celery, bouillon cube, salt and pepper. Bring the soup to a boil. Reduce the heat.
Cover the pan and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
If the soup gets too thick, add a little water.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix and cook together 5 to 8 minutes the raisins, butter, salt, water, sugar and spices.
Dissolve soda in a little hot water.
Add this to raisin mixture.
Add flour until of desired consistency.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Use tube pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chilled avocado and cucumber soup
directions: Peel and seed avocados and cucumbers.
Blend avocados with 1 cup of broth until smooth in food processor or blender.
Stir in lime juice.
Set aside.
Blend cucumbers, remaining 1 cup of broth and chilies until smooth.
Combine with avocado mixture.
Stir in cream and salt to taste.
Serve very cold.
Garnish with chives, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all together with a spoon and pour into a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a large, heavy saucepan.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring, to soft ball stage (238°). Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch pan; cool.
When fudge has set, cut in squares.

title: geri's salad
directions: Drain 2 Cups crushed pineapple.
In saucepan place 1 1/2 Cups sugar, add pineapple and bring to a boil and sugar becomes a syrup.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then last 5.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful and bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend flour, baking soda and baking powder together in a small bowl.
Combine sugars, butters and vanilla extract; blend well. Slowly pour flour mixture into the sugar mixture until all is mixed well.
Roll small balls of cookie mixture into the palms of your hands, then place them on a cookie sheet and press down each ball with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cheese party bits
directions: Mix all together until smooth.
Using melon baller, make small balls.
Place on cookie sheet, cover and freeze.
Store in freezer until ready to use.
Remove from freezer, place on cookie sheet and bake 4 minutes at 450°.
Makes about 90 bits.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add garlic and/or onion salt to taste if desired.

title: mushroom crust quiche
directions: In frying pan over medium heat, saute mushrooms in butter until limp.
Stir in crackers.
Turn into well greased 9-inch pie pan bottom and up sides.
Melt butter; add green onions.
Saute until limp.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over all. In blender whirl cottage cheese with eggs and dash of cayenne pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (knife in center comes out clean).
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail half and half pie crust
directions: Sift salt and flour together in a bowl.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly, but not fine crumbs.
The larger crumbs make the dough flaky.
Add cold water and form into ball.
Roll out on floured cloth (I use a clean dishtowel).
It should be about the consistency of play dough.
Fold dough over in half, ease into pie pan without stretching, trim excess dough or fold under for a thick edge.
Flute, prick all over with fork, bake at 425° for about 10 minutes, or until medium brown.
If a two crust pie is being made, or one in which the filling cooks with the crust, do not punch holes in your bottom crust.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine.
Boil ingredients for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, mixing well.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix with mixer; pour into freezer.
Fill with milk.

title: rice pilaf with black-eyed peas and green beans
directions: Place rice in large bowl with cold water to cover.
With your hands, swish the rice around quickly; pour off most of the water. Repeat 6 to 8 times, or until water is no longer cloudy.
Cover rice with water; set aside 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain, reserving liquid. Mix soup, cheese and vegetable liquid until melted.
Pour over broccoli and mix well.
Place broccoli mixture in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: almost yeast rolls
directions: Mix the flour and sugar in a bowl.
Add the milk and stir together to form soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface and knead 5 to 6 times.
Roll out and cut into squares or use a biscuit cutter.
Place in pan and turn in margarine.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: momma's salsa
directions: Put stewed tomatoes, jalapenos and green chiles in medium size bowl.
Using open end of can, chop them together until peppers are chopped in small pieces and tomato chunks are chopped.
Add garlic and onions.
Mix.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Put chicken in pot and cover with water. Boil until done. Remove bones and skin. Dice meat and put aside. Peel 8 to 10 potatoes. Dice and put in chicken broth. Cook until just about done. Add chicken and about 5 containers of corn. Keep adding until you have the desired amount. Add 1 dozen hard cooked eggs chopped in large pieces. Add salt to taste.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream together butter and both sugars until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: crepes
directions: Pour a little vegetable oil in skillet.
Heat and drain off excess oil.
Pour in Standard Batter and cook until light golden brown on both sides.
We usually eat these rolled with squeezed lemon and sugar on them.
Crepes can be stuffed with fruit, veggies, chicken, etc.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Beat eggs and melt margarine.
Mix together eggs, sugar, margarine and flour. Blend. Add crushed pineapple (undrained) and bread cubes.
Pour into round, buttered baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
While cake is still warm, mix the remaining ingredients and cover the cake.
Use a fork to make holes in the cake for this to soak in.
Later, sprinkle top of cake with sifted powdered sugar.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: In large Dutch oven, melt fat.
Stir in chopped onion.
Cook until pale yellow and soft.
Turn heat to low.
Leave onion in bottom of pan.
Pile shredded cabbage on top.
Sprinkle with bouillon.
Add sliced apples and pepper.
Cut kielbasa into 6 pieces.
Slit each piece about 1/3 way through.
Place on top of apples.
Add potatoes and water.
Cover pan.
Turn heat on high until water boils, then reduce heat to simmer.
After 5 minutes, stir pot.
Continue cooking until cabbage is tender-crisp and vegetables are hot.

title: onion salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients (except oil) in blender and mix well. As blender is running, gradually pour in oil.
Blend until dressing is creamy.
Refrigerate.
Shake well before using.

title: squash dressing
directions: Bake a pan of cornbread; cool.
Boil yellow squash until tender.
Drain.
Chop well.
Boil eggs; set aside.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Crumble cornbread in a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients except chicken broth; mix well. Add broth to mix to desired consistency.
May substitute water for broth (wash out soup cans with it).
May add canned chicken (optional).
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with cranberry sauce, if desired.

title: grilled chicken sandwich
directions: Slice baguette and toast under broiler with olive oil.
Set aside.
Slice chicken into thin layers.
Broil with salt and pepper to taste.
Slice thin yellow pepper, tomato and eggplant. Coat with olive oil.
Broil and flip over for other side.
Spread bread with goat cheese and fill with chicken, pepper, tomato and eggplant.
Eat while warm.

title: stuffed chicken breasts florentina
directions: Defrost spinach; drain.
Squeeze out liquid.
Saute spinach in 1/4 cup Shedd's Spread; set aside.
Wash chicken breasts; drain and dry.
When dry, slice about 1/4 inch under skin across breasts to make a pocket to stuff; set aside.

title: quick black-eyed pea dip(great for new year's eve; microwave)
directions: Drain peas and mash until smooth.
Place in a 1-quart microwavable bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on Medium-high for about 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir well and pour into serving bowl.
Serve with corn chips or crisp raw veggies.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of cake pan.
Spread marshmallows over rhubarb.
Sprinkle box jello over.
Pour mixed cake mix over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix last 3 items together and pour over chicken. Cover and bake about 40 minutes. Uncover and bake until it thickens and chicken is tender. Serve over your choice of rice.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to oil mixture, mixing well.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool for 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mama's light rolls
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water.
Add enough flour to thicken. Let rise.
Sift flour and salt together.
Add shortening.
Then add yeast batter.
Work until it forms a dough.
Do not work until hard.
Let rise until double.
Make into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: lemon icebox pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk in large bowl.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour mixture in pie crust and refrigerate.
This can also be frozen.

title: earl's barbecue sauce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onions to pan, frying until they start to brown.
Add garlic and rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer until sauce thickens.

title: vegetable cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate up to 2 days.
Serve with warm bread or bread sticks.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: You will need a large pan.
Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Use plenty of water up over chicken.
Throw away fat and skins.
Put lean chicken back in broth.
In large mixing bowl, place flour.
Stir in broth to make the dough stiff, but good enough to roll out.
Cut dumplins with pie cutter in small squares. Drop a few drops of yellow cake coloring in broth and chicken. Drop dumplins in hot broth.
Cook slow until done.

title: mom's stuffed cabbage  (sweet and sour)
directions: *If using lemon juice, use 2 tablespoons.

title: grandma's turkey and cornbread dressing
directions: Cook cornbread and let cool.
Break and crumble in large container and toast 1 loaf of white bread and crumble in cornbread.
Cook the chicken or turkey neck and giblets in boiling, salted water until done.
Remove giblets and dice finely. Cook 2 1/2 hours.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add mushrooms, peas and eggs.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Cover with crumbs and bake in a 350° oven until crumbs are brown.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Cook onion and butter. Add mushroom soup; add cheese.
Cook 10 minutes on low.
Add rice and cook 10 minutes.
Chop broccoli in small pieces.
Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: black beauty salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain cherries and reserve liquid.
Add fruit and one half cup cherry juice and other ingredients to gelatin.
If desired, nuts and cherries can be folded in when gelatin is partially jelled to place in artistic design.
This salad can be chilled in individual molds.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and rum until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple with syrup.
Fold together; fill in pie crust and freeze 2 hours or more.

title: diabetic chili
directions: In a 2-1/2 quart pan brown ground beef with salt.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Cook about 2 to 3 minutes over medium heat. Add tomatoes with liquid and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add beans and broth.
Simmer 20 minutes. Yield:
6 servings / 4-1/2 cups.

title: secret cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cook the next 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat. Drop by spoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry-apple relish
directions: Put cranberries and apples through food chopper.
Quarter whole oranges and lemon.
Remove seeds and put through chopper.
Add sugar and blend.
Chill in refrigerator a few hours before serving. Keeps well in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: 9-inch pie pan quiche
directions: Combine eggs, milk and seasoning.
Mix well.
Toss cheese with flour and crumbled bacon.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
You can add green peppers, mushrooms and onions if desired.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients in the order given.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Work into a dough mixture the margarine, brown sugar, flour, salt, peanut butter, white sugar, egg and baking soda.
Put small amount of dough (not even a teaspoonful) into ungreased tassie pan.
Push down flat.
Do not line the sides of tassie pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Drop peanut butter cup into middle of cookie as soon as they come out of the oven. Let stand 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 2 qt. casserole dish combine 1/2 the onion, soup, sour cream, worcestershire sauce and fold in green beans.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onions.
Brown 15 minutes more.

title: flavored squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine and use as crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for a few minutes.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar and spread on crust.

title: blueberry muffins *
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Make hole in mix, add eggs, oil, vanilla and milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Add blueberries. Pour into baking cups and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, bring to a rapid boil the oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add sour milk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Pour in a sheet cake pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch) and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Begin making icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: creamy fruit pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt. Pour into crust. Chill for 4 hours.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, carrots, onion and green pepper in butter until tender but not brown.
Add chicken broth and pepper. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Blend together flour and milk; add cheese and parsley.
Stir into vegetables and broth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: molasses pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, spices and salt; dissolve soda in molasses.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with molasses and milk.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan and bake 325° for 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on cake rack to cool.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In 8-quart saucepan, boil chicken, 1 onion, pepper and 1 tablespoon salt.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Strain 4 cups chicken broth.
When chicken has cooled, remove meat from bones.
Prepare spaghetti as labeled, spread out evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Chop remaining onion and saute mushroom, onion and lemon juice in 2 tablespoon butter. Melt remaining butter in same pan, stir in flour, 2 teaspoons salt, nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon paprika.
Add half and half, chicken and mushroom mixture to chicken broth; heat thoroughly.
Spoon mixture over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash eggplant and cut 1/2-inch thick slices.
Combine egg with water and beat.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Saute in oil until brown and tender.

title: starter
directions: Day 1:
Mix 2 cups flour, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon yeast and 2 cups warm water until smooth.
Cover with loose fitting lid or plastic wrap; allow to stand at room temperature for 8 to 9 hours or overnight.
Refrigerate.
